        OH_HOW_HAVE_YOU_BEEN_YOU_HAVEN_T                                              = 7286,  -- Oh, %. How have you been? You haven't let your stainless steel cooking skills start to rust, have you?
        I_HEARD_FROM_SOME_OF_MY_ACQUAINTANCES_THAT                                    = 7287,  -- I heard from some of my acquaintances that you've become a craftsman at another guild. While I can appreciate your yearning to be a jack-of-all-trades, I am disappointed at your choice not to focus on perfecting your cooking skills.
        THE_CULINARY_ARTS_IS_A_DELICATE_FIELD_A                                       = 7288,  -- The culinary arts is a delicate field. A lack of focus could ruin a whole meal--flatten a whole soufle%i!
        THAT_IS_WHY_I_WARN_YOU_IF_YOU                                                 = 7289,  -- That is why I warn you. If you truly want to become a master chef, you should revoke your craftsman skill status at all other guilds and concentrate on cooking, cooking, and more cooking!
        REVOKE_ALL_OTHER_CRAFTSMAN_STATUSES_RIGHT_AWAY_HOLD                           = 7290,  -- Revoke all other craftsman statuses? Right away. Hold on!
        WONDERFUL_I_CAN_FEEL_THE_FLAMES_OF_YOUR                                       = 7291,  -- Wonderful! I can feel the flames of your heart's oven! Don't worry about contacting the other guilds. I'll notify the proper guildmasters about your decision.
        I_REALIZE_THE_DECISION_IS_A_DIFFICULT_ONE                                     = 7292,  -- I realize the decision is a difficult one, but if you wish to truly master any one thing, there are some sacrifices that cannot be avoided.
        THE_SYNTHESIS_ITEMS_FOR_THAT_RANK_ARE_STILL                                   = 7293,  -- The synthesis items for that rank are still beyond your skill, I'm afraid.
        OUR_CHEF_RETURNS_I_HEAR_YOUR_CULINARY_CREATIONS                               = 7294,  -- Our [veteran/expert/authority/luminary/master] chef returns! I hear your culinary creations are all the rage across town these days. What say you apply a fine garnish to your skills, that you might lead the realm into a new era of epicurean delights?
        HONE_YOUR_SKILLS_FURTHER_CERTAINLY_MAYBE_LATER                                = 7295,  -- Hone your skills further? Certainly! Maybe later...
        NOW_THAT_S_A_SCRUMPTIOUS_ANSWER_FIRST_YOU                                     = 7296,  -- Now that's a scrumptious answer! First, you'll be wanting to acquire a copy of % from Qhum Knaidjn.
        YOU_LL_NEED_A_DASH_OF_GUILD_POINTS                                            = 7297,  -- You'll need a dash of guild points for the transaction, but a chef of your skills should need only a pinch of effort to accrue them.
        WHAT_IS_THIS_FOUL_TASTE_IN_MY_MOUTH                                           = 7298,  -- What is this foul taste in my mouth? Why, I believe it's my bitter disappointment at the potential you're allowing to go to waste.
        FIRST_YOU_LL_WANT_TO_SPEAK_TO_QHUM                                            = 7299,  -- First, you'll want to speak to Qhum Knaidjn and obtain yourself %.
        YOU_RE_BACK_AND_THE_SMILE_ON_YOUR                                             = 7300,  -- You're back, and the smile on your face tells me that you've fully digested the contents of %.
        VERY_WELL_THEN_WASH_YOUR_HANDS_PUT_ON                                         = 7301,  -- Very well, then! Wash your hands, put on your chef's hat, and whip me up %. First you'll have to hunt down the ingredients, of course, a task which I doubt will be as easy as pamama pie.
        AH_AND_DON_T_FORGET_TO_DECORATE_YOUR                                          = 7302,  -- Ah, and don't forget to decorate your dish with your signature, that I and my fellow gourmets will know who to thank for the mouthwatering meal.
        YOU_FORGOT_THE_RECIPE_FOR_I_DON_T                                             = 7303,  -- You forgot the recipe for %? I don't like repeating myself, so be sure to write it down in your cookbook.
        SPLENDID_MARVELOUS_SPECTACULAR_WHY_IT_S_BEEN_YEARS                            = 7304,  -- Splendid! Marvelous! Spectacular! Why, it's been years since I've tasted such a mouthwatering dish! I hereby bestow upon you the rank of expert, and give you my explicit permission to look down your nose at all the faux gourmands around you!
        AN_ADMIRABLE_ATTEMPT_YET_IT_LACKS_A_CERTAIN                                   = 7305,  -- An admirable attempt, yet it lacks a certain...something. Ah, your signature! Do you find your dish so lacking in flavor and pizazz that you are unwilling to take credit for it?
        NO_I_M_AFRAID_THIS_WON_T_DO                                                   = 7306,  -- No, I'm afraid this won't do at all...but you didn't need me to tell you that. Back to the cutting board for you. Chop chop!
        I_THINK_THAT_YOU_ARE_READY_TO_ENTER_2                                         = 7307,  -- I think that you are ready to enter the leagues of the great chefs. Mix me up %.
        IF_IT_TICKLES_MY_TONGUE_I_LL_GRANT_2                                          = 7308,  -- If it tickles my tongue, I'll grant you the title of [artisan/adept/veteran].
        BUT_YOU_MUST_BE_FOREWARNED_BECOMING_OF_THE                                    = 7309,  -- But you must be forewarned. Becoming [an artisan/an adept/a veteran] of the Culinary Guild means a certain level of devotion to the culinary arts.
        YOU_ARE_FREE_TO_BECOME_IN_ANOTHER_GUILD                                       = 7310,  -- You are free to become [an artisan/an adept/a veteran] in another guild, but if doing so means losing that knack you have for cooking...
        AH_YES_AND_WHILE_WE_CANNOT_PREVENT_YOU                                        = 7311,  -- Ah, yes. And while we cannot prevent you from becoming [an artisan/an adept/a veteran] in another guild, I warn you that too much time spent on non-culinary pursuits may cause irreparable harm to your refined palate.
        IS_IT_TRUE_THAT_YOU_VE_ACHIEVED_THE                                           = 7312,  -- Is it true that you've achieved the rank of [artisan/adept/veteran] in a guild other than our own? I must say, %, this leaves a terribly bad taste in my mouth.
        A_CHEF_MUST_BE_FIRST_AND_FOREMOST_A                                           = 7313,  -- A chef must be first and foremost a chef. Waste too much time on idle pursuits and your tarts will lose their tang, your stews their savor!
        LUCKILY_THERE_IS_STILL_TIME_TO_DO_RIGHT                                       = 7314,  -- Luckily, there is still time to do right by your taste buds. Say the word and I can revoke your [artisan/adept/veteran] status in any lesser guilds.
        IT_IS_SIMPLY_A_MATTER_OF_MY_CALLING                                           = 7315,  -- It is simply a matter of my calling the guildmaster and informing them of your desire to focus on your culinary pursuits. So what do you say, %?
        AH_TO_THINK_THAT_I_SHALL_NEVER_AGAIN                                          = 7316,  -- Ah, %. To think that I shall never again know the gustatory bliss that is one of your scrumptious %! It brings a tear to my eye...
        FORGIVE_ME_I_HAVE_NO_DOUBT_THAT_YOU                                           = 7317,  -- Forgive me. I have no doubt that you will be a scrumptious success in whatever profession you choose to follow. Be well, %.
        I_HAVE_BEEN_BURDENED_WITH_THE_DUTY_OF                                         = 7318,  -- I have been burdened with the duty of breaking the following news to all our faithful adventurers, kupo...
        AFTER_LENGTHY_DELIBERATION_THE_MOG_HOUSE_MANAGEMENT_UNION                     = 7319,  -- After lengthy deliberation, the Mog House Management Union (MHMU) has decided upon the cancellation of the Feast of Swords, kupo...
        A_SERIES_OF_SCANDALS_WITHIN_MHMU_S_UPPER                                      = 7320,  -- A series of scandals within MHMU's upper management in recent years has led to the-- Kupopo!?
        THE_MOOGLE_APPEARS_TO_HAVE_RECEIVED_A_MESSAGE                                 = 7321,  -- The moogle appears to have received a message...!
        G_GRAVE_NEWS_KUPO_UNKNOWN_INDIVIDUALS_DONNING_PRICELESS                       = 7322,  -- G-grave news, kupo!!! Unknown individuals donning priceless samurai armor from the Far East have been wreaking havoc!!!
        FURTHERMORE_THESE_SHADY_INDIVIDUALS_CLAIM_THE_ARMOR_WAS                       = 7323,  -- Furthermore, these shady individuals claim the armor was borrowed by the MHMU, kupo!
        PLEASE_LEND_US_A_HAND_BRAVE_ADVENTURER_EQUIP                                  = 7324,  -- Please lend us a hand, brave adventurer! Equip this %, and have a nomad moogle outside town cast special moogle magic upon it, kupo!
        BUT_BE_WARNED_THIS_MAGIC_HAS_THE_SIDE                                         = 7325,  -- But be warned--this magic has the side effect of preventing you from attacking any other monster for three whole Vana'dielian days, kupo!
        THIS_NEW_WEAPON_THE_WAS_DEVELOPED_AS_A                                        = 7326,  -- This new weapon, the %, was developed as a countermeasure for serious situations such as this, kupo. It has been designed with the ability to absorb malicious auras emitted by enemies.
        WE_WANT_YOU_TO_USE_IT_TO_ABSORB                                               = 7327,  -- We want you to use it to absorb malice from those wacky samurai wannabes, and then plant this % near where they fall. By doing so, you can further weaken the insidious individuals inside the armor, kupo!
        TO_PLANT_THE_ALL_YOU_HAVE_TO_DO                                               = 7328,  -- To plant the %, all you have to do is trade it to the ground near a fallen fiend. You'll get a reward that matches the amount of malice absorbed, kupo!
        WHEN_YOU_PLANT_THE_INTO_THE_GROUND_ALL                                        = 7329,  -- When you plant the % into the ground, all malice absorbed inside will be purified by the land, kupo!
        ALRIGHT_THEN_TAKE_THIS_AND_GET_TO_WORK                                        = 7330,  -- Alright then! Take this % and get to work on those vile villains! I'll be preparing your special reward, kupo!
        EQUIP_THIS_AND_HAVE_A_NOMAD_MOOGLE_OUTSIDE                                    = 7331,  -- Equip this %, and have a nomad moogle outside town cast special moogle magic upon it. Be sure to absorb as much malice as you can from those scoundrels, kupo!
        GOOD_JOB_KUPO_YOU_SURE_SHOWED_THEM_WHO                                        = 7332,  -- Good job, kupo! You sure showed them who's boss! Thanks to you, we were able to avoid a diplomatic disaster with the Far East, kupo.
        A_HANDFUL_OF_NO_GOOD_NOMAD_MOOGLES_AND                                        = 7333,  -- A handful of no-good nomad moogles and Goblins were conspiring to take over the MHMU, wilfully assuming false identities in order to obtain the armor and frame us, kupo!
        THEN_THEY_HIRED_THIEVES_TO_WEAR_THE_ARMOR                                     = 7334,  -- Then, they hired thieves to wear the armor and do their dirty work!
        BUT_THANKS_TO_ALL_YOU_COURAGEOUS_ADVENTURERS_THE                              = 7335,  -- But thanks to all you courageous adventurers, the MHMU is safe and sound, kupo!
        WE_NEED_YOUR_HELP_TO_CLEAR_THE_LAND                                           = 7336,  -- We need your help to clear the land of the malice-emitting menace, kupo!
        YOU_HAVE_EQUIPPED_GREAT_NOW_HOLD_STILL_WHILE                                  = 7337,  -- You have % equipped! Great! Now, hold still while I cast miraculously marvelous moogle magic on it, kupo.
