        YOU_LOOK_NEW_TO_THESE_PARTS_I_GUESS                                           = 7511,  -- You look new to these parts. I guess we should introduce ourselves to each other-wother. This is the north gatehouse, and we're the guards whose duty it is to protect Windurst.
        HUH_YOU_HAVE_SOME_KIND_OF_BUSINESS_WITH                                       = 7512,  -- Huh? You have some kind of business with us, the North Winds? Mokyokyo is our leader-weader, so speak to her first.
        OH_A_FOREIGNER_HUH_IF_YOU_RE_LOOKING                                          = 7513,  -- Oh, a foreigner, huh? If you're looking for the [San d'Orian/Bastokan] Consulate, then head [yonder southeast/south]... It's in [Windurst Woods/Port Windurst]. Ta-taru.
        THISS_THEORTH_GATEHOUSE_EN_IS_CARDIANSSIGNED_TOHE_NORTHINDS                   = 7514,  -- tHIsS tHeOrTh gATeHOusE!En IS CArDiANSsiGNed tOHe NOrThInDs gUaRds!
        YOUANT_TOOIN_NORTHIND_GUARDSOO_HEN_SPEAKO_THEEADER_MOKYOKYO                   = 7515,  -- yOuaNt tOoIn NOrTHinD gUaRdsOo?HeN sPeAkO tHeEaDer, MoKyoKyo!
        IF_YOU_RE_A_CITIZEN_OF_WINDURST_THEN                                          = 7516,  -- If you're a citizen of Windurst, then pleasey-weasey sign up for your first mission here! We're having a bet with the other gatehouses over who can gainy-wainy the most new recruits.
        ERROR_SAYING_A_MASKED_ANSWER                                                  = 7517,  -- ERROR: SAYING A MASKED ANSWER!
        YOU_CANNOT_ACCEPT_MORE_THAN_ONE_MISSION_AT                                    = 7518,  -- You cannot accept more than one mission at a timey-wimey. Please complete your current mission before applying for the next.
        I_SHALL_NOW_READ_OUT_THE_MISSIONS_YOU                                         = 7519,  -- I shall now read out the missions you are able to receive...
        WHICH_MISSION_WILL_YOU_ACCEPT_THE_HORUTOTO_RUINS                              = 7520,  -- Which mission will you accept? The Horutoto Ruins Experiment. The Heart of the Matter. The Price of Peace. Lost for Words. A Testing Time. The Three Kingdoms. Mission 2-3-1A. Mission 2-3-1B. Mission 2-3-2A. Mission 2-3-2B. To Each His Own Right. Written in the Stars. A New Journey. Magicite. The Final Seal. The Shadow Awaits. Full Moon Fountain. Saintly Invitation. The Sixth Ministry. Awakening of the Gods. Vain. The Jester Who'd Be King. Doll of the Dead. Moon Reading. Dummy11. Dummy12. Dummy13. Dummy14. Dummy15. Dummy16. Dummy17. Decline mission.
        WAS_MISS_APURURU_WELL                                                         = 7521,  -- Was Miss Apururu well?
        IF_MISS_APURURU_IS_WELL_THEN_I_M                                              = 7522,  -- If Miss Apururu is well, then I'm happy-wappy.
        IF_THERE_S_SOMETHING_YOU_DON_T_UNDERSTAND                                     = 7523,  -- If there's something you don't understand, just ask Jack of Hearts for a hand. You can find him in the plaza in fronty-wonty of the Optistery.
        AND_EVEN_THEN_IF_YOU_STILL_DON_T                                              = 7524,  -- And even then, if you still don't understand something, pluck up the courage and ask your fellow adventurers for advice.
        THISS_THEORTH_GATEHOUSE_EN_AM_CARDIANSSIGNED_TO_THE                           = 7525,  -- tHIsS tHeOrTh gATeHOusE!En AM CArDiANSsiGNed tO tHe NOrTh WInDsUaRds!
        CAN_YOU_STAND_ON_YOUR_OWN_TWO_FEETSY                                          = 7526,  -- Can you stand on your own two feetsy-weetsy as an adventurer yet?
        IF_SO_THEN_YOU_SHOULD_HELP_OUT_OTHER                                          = 7527,  -- If so, then you should help out other new adventurers. Kindness is the most whooper-dooper magic that anyone can use.
        THE_FOUR_GATEHOUSES_ARE_COMPETING_OVER_WHO_CAN                                = 7528,  -- The four gatehouses are competing over who can get the most new recruits. I wonder how it's going.
        I_BET_WE_NORTH_WINDS_ARE_WINNING_T                                            = 7529,  -- I bet we North Winds are winning!t
        HELLO_THERE_WELCOME_TO_THE_NORTH_WINDS                                        = 7530,  -- Hello there. Welcome to the North Winds.
        HAVE_YOU_CHECKED_OUT_THE_REST_OF_WINDURST                                     = 7531,  -- Have you checked out the rest of Windurst, yet? There are several gatehouses spread all over this city-wity.
        THIS_IS_THE_NORTH_GATEHOUSE_OUR_GROUP_THAT                                    = 7532,  -- This is the north gatehouse. Our group that gathers here at Odin's Gate goes by the name of the North Winds.
        HUH_YOU_DON_T_KNOW_ABOUT_GATEHOUSES_WELL                                      = 7533,  -- Huh? You don't know about gatehouses? Well, you're going to find the going tough if you don't learn soon. Want me to explainy-wainy...?
        HEAR_THE_EXPLANATION_YES_PLEASEY_WEASEY_NO_THANKY                             = 7534,  -- Hear the explanation? Yes, pleasey-weasey. No, thanky-hanky.
        THE_GATEHOUSES_ARE_MEETING_AND_RESTING_POINTS_FOR                             = 7535,  -- The gatehouses are meeting and resting points for us guards who protect Windurst.
        THEY_ARE_ALSO_THE_PLACES_WHERE_MISSIONS_FROM                                  = 7536,  -- They are also the places where missions from the Federation of Windurst are received and allocated to people.
        WHEN_YOU_RECEIVE_A_MISSION_AND_SUCCESSFULLY_COMPLETE                          = 7537,  -- When you receive a mission and successfully complete the task it involves, you will be awarded rank points.
        COLLECT_ENOUGH_RANK_POINTS_AND_YOUR_RANK_OR                                   = 7538,  -- Collect enough rank points, and your rank, or relative position in society, will rise.
        AT_FIRST_YOU_MIGHT_ONLY_RECEIVE_BORING_MISSIONS                               = 7539,  -- At first you might only receive boring missions, but even those have their good side, allowing you to meet with people you would not normally be able to, and so on.
        SO_HOW_ABOUT_IT_ARE_YOU_INTERESTED_IN                                         = 7540,  -- So how about it? Are you interested in serving your country? We really recommend you try them outy-wouty.
        RECEIVE_A_MISSION_ACCEPT_DECLINE                                              = 7541,  -- Receive a mission? Accept. Decline.
        DON_T_NEED_TO_HEAR_THE_EXPLANATION_HUH                                        = 7542,  -- Don't need to hear the explanation, huh? Oh, so you consider yourself a scholar-wolar or something? Well we'll see about thatty-watty.
        SO_HOW_ABOUT_IT_THEN_TRY_YOUR_HAND                                            = 7543,  -- So how about it then? Try your hand out at a mission?
        YOU_RE_A_CITIZEN_OF_WINDURST_SO_YOU                                           = 7544,  -- You're a citizen of Windurst, so you can receive missions here.
        THAT_S_THE_SPIRIT_WIRIT_LOOKS_LIKE_IT                                         = 7545,  -- That's the spirit-wirit! Looks like it's my cue... I have a mission just right for you, so listen up!
        YOU_KNOW_THE_HORUTOTO_RUINS_OUT_IN_SARUTABARUTA                               = 7546,  -- You know the Horutoto Ruins out in Sarutabaruta, don't you? Well, they're about to conduct some kind of magic experiment there.
        THE_ORASTERY_ONE_OF_THE_FIVE_MINISTRIES_OF                                    = 7547,  -- The Orastery, one of the five ministries of Windurst, is urgently requesting the dispatch of an adventurer to help them out.
        ASK_THE_ORASTERY_S_MINISTER_AT_THEIR_MAGE                                     = 7548,  -- Ask the Orastery's minister at their Mage Academy for the details.
        THE_ORASTERY_S_MAGE_ACADEMY_IS_A_BIG                                          = 7549,  -- The Orastery's Mage Academy is a big building in Port Windurst, far to the south of here. Well, good luck with your first tasky-wasky!
        I_GUESS_THERE_S_NO_RUSHY_WUSHY_YOU                                            = 7550,  -- I guess there's no rushy-wushy. You'll be better prepared to complete your missions the more familiar you are with Windurst.
        COME_BACK_WHEN_YOU_FEEL_READY_WEADY_WE                                        = 7551,  -- Come back when you feel ready-weady. We'll be waiting for you.
        OH_MY_OH_WHY_WELL_THAT_TOOK_THE                                               = 7552,  -- Oh my, oh why...? Well, that took the wind out of our sails...
        I_SUPPOSE_YOU_ONLY_JUST_ARRIVED_IN_WINDURST                                   = 7553,  -- I suppose you only just arrived in Windurst and want to see more of the area, so it's understandable. Come back when you're ready-weady.
        WELL_THEN_HURRY_ON_OVER_TO_THE_ORASTERY                                       = 7554,  -- Well then, hurry on over to the Orastery. It sounds like the Orastery is going to conduct some kind of magic experiment in the magic towers.
        THE_MINISTER_OF_THE_ORASTERY_WILL_EXPLAIN_THE                                 = 7555,  -- The Minister of the Orastery will explain the details.
        HMM_MY_FIRST_TASK_WAS_TO_CLEAN_UP                                             = 7556,  -- Hmm... My first task was to clean up the garbage in Sarutabaruta. Thinking back now...boy, those days were peaceful!
        HURRY_ON_OVER_TO_THE_ORASTERY_IT_S                                            = 7557,  -- Hurry on over to the Orastery. It's the big building in Port Windurst, far to the south of here.
        LUCKY_YOU_SOUNDS_LIKE_AN_EXCITING_MISSION_WITH                                = 7558,  -- Lucky you. Sounds like an exciting mission with that magic experiment going on. But, oh, I forgot! The Minister of the Orastery is THAT guy...
        THE_MINISTER_OF_THE_ORASTERY_WILL_TELL_YOU                                    = 7559,  -- The Minister of the Orastery will tell you what the mission entails.
        NOW_THAT_YOU_MENTION_IT_THERE_S_BEEN                                          = 7560,  -- Now that you mention it, there's been an awful lot of these experiments going on lately. What is the Orastery up to this time?
        HORUTOTO_RUINS_DANGEROUSLACE                                                  = 7561,  -- hOrUtOtO RuInS... DaNgERoUsLaCE!
        BAD_CARDIANSURK_INOME_PARTS_BEARE_FUL_NOTO_GOO                                = 7562,  -- BAD cArDiaNsUrK iNOMe PaRTs! beArE-ful nOtO goO WroNGlaCe!
        GOOD_TO_SEE_YOU_MADE_IT_BACKY_WACKY                                           = 7563,  -- Good to see you made it backy-wacky. Looks like you did well for your first task. We'll allocate you rank points according to our evaluation of your mission.
        WE_LOOK_FORWARD_TO_YOU_ASSISTING_US_WITH                                      = 7564,  -- We look forward to you assisting us with our next task.
        IT_MIGHT_NOT_FEEL_LIKE_YOU_RE_ACHIEVING                                       = 7565,  -- It might not feel like you're achieving much at firsty-wirsty, but your efforts are contributing to the peace of Windurst.
        I_M_SURE_MY_TELLING_YOU_THAT_SUDDENLY                                         = 7566,  -- I'm sure my telling you that suddenly enthused you, didn't it?
        THANK_YOU_FOR_YOUR_CONTINUING_SERVICE_WE_HOPE                                 = 7567,  -- Thank you for your continuing service. We hope you'll keep up the effort by helping us out with our next task.
        THANK_YOUOR_YOURATRIOTISM_YOU_COMPLETEDOUR_MISSIONELL_ANDAVE_RECEIVEDANK      = 7568,  -- ThAnK yOuOr yOuRatRIOTism! YoU cOmPleTEdoUR miSsIoNElL aNdAvE rEcEIvEdAnk pOINts!
        YOUAN_CONFIRM_YOUR_POINTSY_CHECKING_YOUR2PROFILEN_THE2STATUSPTION_ON          = 7569,  -- YoUAn CoNfIrm YoUr PoiNTsY cHeCKinG yOuR2PROFILEn the2STATUSPtIoN on tHe2MAIN MENU!
        YOUR_PREVIOUS_MISSION_WAS_THE_ORASTERY_S_MAGIC                                = 7570,  -- Your previous mission was the Orastery's magic experiment, right? Well then, this next tasky-wasky should be a piece of cake.
        THE_MANUSTERY_IS_CURRENTLY_LOOKING_FOR_AN_ADVENTURER                          = 7571,  -- The Manustery is currently looking for an adventurer to help them in Cardian creation. Do you accept this mission?
        ACCEPT_THIS_MISSION_ACCEPT_DECLINE                                            = 7572,  -- Accept this mission? Accept. Decline.
        ASK_THE_STAFF_AT_THE_CARDIAN_WORKSHOP_IN                                      = 7573,  -- Ask the staff at the Cardian workshop in the Manustery for the details of this mission.
        HUH_YOU_DON_T_KNOW_WHERE_THE_MANUSTERY                                        = 7574,  -- Huh? You don't know where the Manustery is? Would you understand if I said it's near the round in Windurst Woods, the district where all those Mithra live?
        THE_MANUSTERY_S_CARDIAN_WORKSHOP_IS_SOUTHEAST_OF                              = 7575,  -- The Manustery's Cardian workshop is southeast of here, in Windurst Woods.
        TO_GET_TO_WINDURST_WOODS_YOU_HAVE_TO                                          = 7576,  -- To get to Windurst Woods, you have to pass through either Windurst Walls to the east, or Port Windurst to the south.
        IT_S_A_LONG_WAY_TO_WALK_BUT                                                   = 7577,  -- It's a long way to walk, but it's a good chance to get to know our country. Check your map to find the way, then consider it a leisurely strolly-wolly.
        I_CAN_T_HIDE_THE_FACT_THAT_I                                                  = 7578,  -- I can't hide the fact that I'm a big fan of Apururu from the Manustery!
        SHE_S_ALWAYS_SO_NICE_AND_KINDY_WINDY                                          = 7579,  -- She's always so nice and kindy-windy, never failing to show her shining smiley-wiley, despite her tragic past.
        LISTEN_HERE_YOU_BETTER_COMPLETE_APURURU_S_MISSION                             = 7580,  -- Listen here! You better complete Apururu's mission as fasty-wasty and as perfectly-werfectly as possible. Don't you dare mess up! You got it?
        CARDIANS_ARE_OUR_AUTOMATON_GUARDS_THEY_WERE_ORIGINALLY                        = 7581,  -- Cardians are our automaton guards. They were originally created twenty years ago by Zonpa-Zippa, the Minister of the Manustery.
        IT_S_HARD_ENOUGH_TO_COLLECT_THE_MATERIALS                                     = 7582,  -- It's hard enough to collect the materials to make them, but it takes even more effort to train them. Occasionally a few go bonkers-wonkers and run away...or that's what the guys from the Manustery say.
        MORENTELLIGENT_CARDIANSECOME_WINDURST_SOWN_GUARDS_TRONGERARDIANS_PATROLUTSIDE = 7583,  -- mOrENtElLiGEnt CArdiAnsECoMe WInDUrsT'sOwn GUarDs!TroNgerARdiaNS PATrolUtsIDe!
        WHATAP_PENS_TOMARTEST_ANDTRONGEST_CARDIANS                                    = 7584,  -- wHaTaP-pEnS tOMArTEst aNdTroNgEst cARdIAns...?
        THEYECOME_THECE_CARDIANSHAT_GUARDEAVENS_TOWER                                 = 7585,  -- ...theYEcOme tHeCE CArDiaNsHAt guArDeAVeNs ToWeR!
        HAVE_YOU_BECOME_COMFORTABLE_WITH_PERFORMING_MISSIONS_YET                      = 7586,  -- Have you become comfortable with performing missions yet?
        TODAY_I_M_THINKING_ABOUT_ASKING_YOU_TO                                        = 7587,  -- Today, I'm thinking about asking you to do a very-wery important mission.
        YOUR_DESTINATION_WILL_BE_GIDDEUS_IT_S_WHERE                                   = 7588,  -- Your destination will be Giddeus. It's where the Yagudo beastmen dwell, on the other side of West Sarutabaruta.
        DO_YOU_KNOW_MUCH_ABOUT_THE_YAGUDO_WINDURST                                    = 7589,  -- Do you know much about the Yagudo? Windurst fought them in the war twenty years ago, but we currently maintain amicable relations.
        AS_A_SIGN_OF_OUR_FRIENDSHIP_WE_PROVIDE                                        = 7590,  -- As a sign of our friendship, we provide them with food offerings. That about sums up your mission-wission.
        THE_RHINOSTERY_PREPARES_THE_FOOD_OFFERINGS_YOU_CAN                            = 7591,  -- The Rhinostery prepares the food offerings. You can pick them up at the biological laboratory here at the south side of Windurst Waters.
        ONCE_YOU_HAVE_RECEIVED_THE_FOOD_OFFERINGS_FROM                                = 7592,  -- Once you have received the food offerings from the researchers there, you should head straight to Giddeus.
        I_DON_T_WANT_YOU_TO_GET_WORKED                                                = 7593,  -- I don't want you to get worked up about it, but this mission could affect the future of Windurst. It's that important!
        PLEASE_BE_EXTREMELY_CAREFUL                                                   = 7594,  -- Please be extremely careful!
        FIRST_HEAD_TO_THE_RHINOSTERY_S_BIOLOGICAL_LABORATORY                          = 7595,  -- First, head to the Rhinostery's biological laboratory here in the south of Windurst Waters.
        ONCE_YOU_HAVE_RECEIVED_THE_FOOD_OFFERINGS_FROM_2                              = 7596,  -- Once you have received the food offerings from the researchers there, go straight to the food offering altars in Giddeus. Exercise the utmost caution-waution!
        I_KNOW_WE_SHOULDN_T_ASK_THIS_BUT                                              = 7597,  -- I know we shouldn't ask this, but... Why do we have to provide the Yagudo with all this stuff anyway?
        THE_BEASTMAN_HORDES_WERE_UTTERLY_DEFEATED_BY_OUR                              = 7598,  -- The beastman hordes were utterly defeated by our allied forces in the war twenty years ago, weren't they? So what's the dealy-wealy?
        MAKE_NO_MISTAKEY_WAKEYS_ALTHOUGH_WE_RE_SUPPOSED                               = 7599,  -- Make no mistakey-wakeys! Although we're supposed to be on friendly terms with the Yagudo, Giddeus is still a dangerous dungeon.
        EVEN_IF_YOU_EXPLAIN_THAT_YOU_RE_SIMPLY                                        = 7600,  -- Even if you explain that you're simply a messenger from Windurst, they'll say that they have to test you to determine the truth. Then they all start to attack you.
        OF_COURSE_IF_YOU_STEP_IN_THERE_WITHOUT                                        = 7601,  -- Of course, if you step in there without any real reason, they'll claim that you're encroaching on their sacred territory, and attack you in full force. They are most irritating.
        THIS_MISSIONS_VERYMPORTANT_SOHEN_YOUINISH_ITOU_CANXPECT_AEWARD                = 7602,  -- THis MIsSiOnS VeRyMpOrTaNt sOHeN YoUInIsh iTOu cAnxPecT aeWArd!
        BUTON_T_OVERDOT_YOU_ONLYAVE_ONEIFE_IFOU_GOOO                                  = 7603,  -- BuTOn'T oVeRdoT! yoU ONlyAVe oNeiFe! IfOu GoOO fAroU mAyEVeR rEtUrN!
        TWHAT_SPEAK_UP_WHAT_S_THAT_YOU_SAY                                            = 7604,  -- tWhat? Speak up! What's that you say? You're the help from the gatehouse, eh?
        WAIT_RIGHT_HERE_IF_YOU_DON_T_MIND                                             = 7605,  -- Wait right here, if you don't mind... I'll go get it, from out behind.
        HERE_YOU_GO_SORRY_FOR_ALL_THE_FUSS                                            = 7606,  -- Here you go... Sorry for all the fuss. Today's offering for the altars of Giddeus.
        IN_THESE_BAGS_ARE_YAGUDO_S_FAVORITE_CHERRIES                                  = 7607,  -- In these bags are Yagudo's favorite cherries. These should give those ugly old beastmen their merries.
        IF_YOU_ARE_WONDERING_WHY_THERE_RE_NOW                                         = 7608,  -- If you are wondering why there're now two bags, it's 'cause there're two altars in Giddeus's crags. A Yagudo by each altar stands. To each of them a bag you hand.
        AND_THOUGH_AN_OFFERING_YOU_DO_BEAR_THOSE                                      = 7609,  -- And though an offering you do bear, those Yagudo may attack you there. So take precautions, be prepared... Lest you return in states impaired!t
        THE_PLACES_WHERE_THE_ALTARS_OF_OFFERING_STAND                                 = 7610,  -- The places where the altars of offering stand, are a little way into the Giddeus land. Before the entrances of the caves they are, so be careful not to venture in too far.
        AND_THOUGH_AN_OFFERING_YOU_DO_BEAR_THOSE_2                                    = 7611,  -- And though an offering you do bear, those Yagudo may attack you there. So be prepared and best of luck, unless you are a lucky...schmuck.t
        YOU_RE_THE_ADVENTURER_WHO_ACCEPTED_OUR_MISSION                                = 7612,  -- You're the adventurer who accepted our mission for today? Leepe-Hoppe has prepared the food offerings for you to take to Giddeus. He's waiting on the rooftop orchard right above us.
        TO_GET_TO_THE_ROOF_GO_OUTSIDE_AND                                             = 7613,  -- To get to the roof, go outside and take the stairs on the side of the building.
        AT_FIRST_THERE_WAS_JUST_ONE_ALTAR_FOR                                         = 7614,  -- At first there was just one altar for offerings in Giddeus. So we only needed to take one bag of food.
        THEN_ONE_DAY_THOSE_SNEAKY_YAGUDO_DECIDED_TO                                   = 7615,  -- Then one day, those sneaky Yagudo decided to build another altar. They are so greedy.
        FOOD_BAG_OFFERING                                                             = 7616,  -- Food...bag...offering...
        FROM_CULI_NARIANS_GUILD                                                       = 7617,  -- from...Culi...narians'...Guild...
        HAS_JUICE_IN_IT                                                               = 7618,  -- has...juice...in...it...!
        WE_OF_THE_RHINOSTERY_WOULD_LIKE_TO_EXPLORE                                    = 7619,  -- We of the Rhinostery would like to explore the underground canals too.
        AND_INVESTIGATE_WHY_THE_GREAT_BEAST_DISAPPEARED_AFTER                         = 7620,  -- And investigate why the great beast disappeared after the war ceased.
        BUT_THE_ENTRANCE_TO_THE_CANALS_IN_WINDURST                                    = 7621,  -- But the entrance to the canals in Windurst Walls, has been off-limits for twenty years, 'spite our calls. Known only as the Priming Gate, Cardians guard it as of late.
        I_KNOW_I_KNOW_THAT_S_WHY_I                                                    = 7622,  -- I know, I know. That's why I'm asking you for your cooperation.
        OUR_OBJECTIVES_COINCIDE_I_M_IN_SEARCH_OF                                      = 7623,  -- Our objectives coincide... I'm in search of Karaha-Baruha's laboratory, and you're in search of the great beast's lair.
        BUT_OPENING_THE_PRIMING_GATE_IS_NO_EASY                                       = 7624,  -- But opening the Priming Gate is no easy thing, the key is our Rhinostery minister's ring. And Minister Rukususu wouldn't to you lend, her ring even if you were really her friend.
        YOU_DON_T_GET_WHAT_I_M_SAYING                                                 = 7625,  -- You don't get what I'm saying. That's why I'm asking you! Listen. On the night Rukususu comes back from the Northlands...
        LET_S_CONTINUE_THIS_DISCUSSION_LATER_TA_TARU                                  = 7626,  -- ...Let's continue this discussion later! Ta-taru!
        BACK_FROM_GIDDEUS_NOW_I_SEE_YOUR_MISSION                                      = 7627,  -- Back from Giddeus now, I see! Your mission's done. What joy, what glee!
        OH_THAT_WAS_THE_ORASTERY_MINISTER_AJIDO_MARUJIDO                              = 7628,  -- Oh, that was the Orastery minister, Ajido-Marujido, who wants to go to Karaha-Baruha's lab in the canals so...
        SO_IT_REALLY_IS_THE_TRUTH_WHAT_THE                                            = 7629,  -- So it really is the truth, what the rumors say... he's been asking about forbidden magic today.
        I_M_SURPRISED_HE_DOESN_T_GET_CAUGHT                                           = 7630,  -- I'm surprised he doesn't get caught without quibble, by Windurst's Sibyl Guards and the great Star Sibyl.
        ANYWAY_YOUR_TASK_S_COMPLETE_YOUR_MISSION_DONE                                 = 7631,  -- Anyway, your task's complete, your mission done, so return to the gatehouse where you begun.
        HA_HA_I_M_SURE_SOMETHING_GREAT_AWAITS                                         = 7632,  -- Ha-ha! I'm sure something great, awaits you back at the gate!
        WELL_YOUR_TASK_S_COMPLETE_YOUR_MISSION_DONE                                   = 7633,  -- Well, your task's complete, your mission done. Return to the gatehouse where you begun.
        HA_HA_I_M_SURE_SOMETHING_GREAT_AWAITS_2                                       = 7634,  -- Ha-ha! I'm sure something great, awaits you back at the gate!
        WELL_DONE_RELIEVED_TO_SEE_YOU_MADE_IT                                         = 7635,  -- Well done. Relieved to see you made it back in one piecey-wiecey.
        AND_CONGRATULATIONS_ARE_IN_ORDER_YOU_HAVE_SUCCESSFULLY                        = 7636,  -- And congratulations are in order! You have successfully completed three missions, and have received enough rank points to go up in rank.
        NOW_THAT_YOU_MADE_RANK_TWO_YOU_CAN                                            = 7637,  -- Now that you made rank two, you can participate in conquests. To find out more about conquests, ask one of the conquest guards.
        YOU_NEED_TO_GAIN_RANK_POINTS_BY_PARTICIPATING                                 = 7638,  -- You need to gain rank points by participating in conquests before you can receive any further missions.
        LET_S_KEEP_WORKING_TOGETHER_FOR_THE_SAKE                                      = 7639,  -- Let's keep working together for the sake of Windurst.
        YOU_WERE_ABLE_TO_DELIVER_THE_GOODS_TO                                         = 7640,  -- You were able to deliver the goods to Giddeus, huh? Congratulations! That means you're now rank two!
        THE_HIGHER_WIGHER_YOU_GO_UP_IN_RANK                                           = 7641,  -- The higher-wigher you go up in rank, the harder-warder the missions become.
        AND_YOU_HAVE_TO_BOLDLY_RUSH_INTO_PLACES                                       = 7642,  -- And you have to boldly rush into places where angels fear to tread. It really is tough!
        WHOA_YOU_RE_ALIVE_ARE_YOU_SURE_YOU                                            = 7643,  -- Whoa! You're alive? Are you sure you're not a ghosty-whosty?
