        YOUR_REWARD                                                                   = 8117,  -- ...... ...Your...reward...
        ID_8118                                                                       = 8118,  -- ...?
        SEEDS                                                                         = 8119,  -- ...Seeds...
        OF_FLUORO_FLORA                                                               = 8120,  -- ...of...fluoro-flora...
        I_WAS_WONDERING_WHAT_HE_WAS_ASKING_YOU                                        = 8121,  -- I was wondering what he was asking you to do. Now I see it was bringing him the cargo shipped in via Mhaura.
        I_HOPE_YOU_KEPT_TO_THE_TIME_LIMIT                                             = 8122,  -- I hope you kept to the time limit. Those things are extremely hard to handle.
        YOU_VE_SEEN_THE_FLOWERS_ALL_OVER_WINDURST                                     = 8123,  -- You've seen the flowers all over Windurst that serve as streetlights, right?
        THOSE_FLOWERS_ARE_CALLED_FLUORO_FLORA_WE_CAST                                 = 8124,  -- Those flowers are called fluoro-flora. We cast magic on their seeds to enhance their illumination.
        BUT_THE_NEEDED_TO_CARRY_OUT_OUR_ENHANCING                                     = 8125,  -- But the % needed to carry out our enhancing work is running in short supply.
        COULD_I_DARE_ASK_YOU_TO_OBTAIN_FOR                                            = 8126,  -- Could I dare ask you to obtain % for us? I must warn you, it involves going to some dangerous territory!
        GO_FETCH_SOME_WATER_YES_NO                                                    = 8127,  -- Go fetch some water? Yes. No.
        THANK_YOU_PLEASE_FILL_THIS_CANTEEN_FULL_OF                                    = 8128,  -- Thank you. Please fill this canteen full of water from the springs at the back of Giddeus.
        THE_DEPTHS_OF_GIDDEUS_ARE_INDEED_DANGEROUS_SO                                 = 8129,  -- The depths of Giddeus are indeed dangerous, so I don't blame you for backing out.
        PARTS_OF_GIDDEUS_CAN_GET_CONFUSING_SO_I                                       = 8130,  -- Parts of Giddeus can get confusing, so I recommend you check a map as you go.
        AH_IT_WOULD_BE_UNTHINKABLE_TO_TRY_TO                                          = 8131,  -- Ah, it would be unthinkable to try to go there alone. You should gather a few competent adventurer friends so you can travel together. But don't worry. Your remuneration will be most handsome.
        WHAT_YOU_LOST_MY_CANTEEN_HERE_TAKE_ANOTHER                                    = 8132,  -- What? You lost my canteen? Here, take another. But be more careful with people's things, okay?
        OH_WELL_DONE                                                                  = 8133,  -- Oh! Well done!
        RIGHT_ON_TIME_TOO_I_WAS_DOWN_TO                                               = 8134,  -- Right on time, too. I was down to my last drop.
        HERE_S_YOUR_REMUNERATION_PLEASE_HELP_US_OUT                                   = 8135,  -- Here's your remuneration. Please help us out again the next time our supply dwindles.
        CURRENTLY_WE_CAN_ONLY_OBTAIN_FROM_THE_SPRINGS                                 = 8136,  -- Currently, we can only obtain % from the springs at the back of Giddeus. However, the magic of that water has weakened considerably.
        WE_USED_TO_BE_ABLE_TO_FIND_STRONGER                                           = 8137,  -- We used to be able to find stronger magic water in another place, but that was before the war...
        WHAT_IT_LOOKS_LIKE_I_VE_BEEN_SLEEPING                                         = 8138,  -- What? It looks like I've been sleeping all day and haven't done any work?
        HOW_RUDE_DESPITE_MY_APPEARANCE_I_M_A                                          = 8139,  -- How rude! Despite my appearance, I'm a brilliant and busy researcher who is feeling quite hard-pressed at the moment.
        I_SPECIALIZE_IN_THE_STUDY_OF_THE_HEART                                        = 8140,  -- I specialize in the study of the heart and soul. You've heard the saying, Illness arises from the sickness of the spirit, right? Well, I'm researching the spirit part of that.
        WHENEVER_SOMETHING_STRANGE_HAPPENS_PEOPLE_CALL_ME_FOR                         = 8141,  -- Whenever something strange happens, people call me. For instance, if you find a suspicious item, you should bring it to me to check.
        WHAT_S_THIS_GRUBBY_LITTLE_RIBBON_YOU_BROUGHT                                  = 8142,  -- What's this grubby little ribbon you brought me? Huh? You can hear strange voices?
        NOW_THAT_IS_PECULIAR_PLEASE_GIVE_IT_TO                                        = 8143,  -- Now that is peculiar! Please give it to me. I'll pay you # gil for it.
        I_ENJOY_COLLECTING_STRANGE_OR_MYSTERIOUS_THINGS_IT                            = 8144,  -- I enjoy collecting strange or mysterious things. It's part of my job to investigate them.
        HEY_YOU_YOU_SHOULD_TAKE_RESPONSIBILITY_FOR_YOUR                               = 8145,  -- Hey, you! You should take responsibility for your evil actions!
        THIS_RIBBON_BELONGS_TO_A_DECEASED_PERSON_WHOSE                                = 8146,  -- This ribbon belongs to a deceased person whose body now rests in a grave somewhere. I don't care how poor you are! Grave-robbing is just plain criminal!
        WHAT_DO_YOU_MEAN_YOU_DIDN_T_STEAL                                             = 8147,  -- What do you mean, you didn't steal it? It was passed around until it came to you?
        WELL_NOW_THAT_IT_HAS_FALLEN_INTO_YOUR                                         = 8148,  -- Well, now that it has fallen into your hands, you should return it to its rightful owner. I'm sure the poor old soul who lost this misses it greatly.
        THAT_CAME_FROM_A_GRAVE_SOMEWHERE_IT_BELONGS                                   = 8149,  -- That % came from a grave somewhere. It belongs to a dead person.
        YOU_SHOULD_RETURN_IT_TO_ITS_RIGHTFUL_PLACE                                    = 8150,  -- You should return it to its rightful place. I'm sure the poor old soul who lost this misses it greatly.
        YOU_WERE_ABLE_TO_PURIFY_THAT_CURSED_RIBBON                                    = 8151,  -- You were able to purify that cursed ribbon? Well, that is good news. It was so noisy every night, I could hardly sleep.
        TONIGHT_I_LL_BE_ABLE_TO_SLEEP_WELL                                            = 8152,  -- Tonight, I'll be able to sleep well and have pleasant dreams. Well, time to get some well-earned sleep. Goodbye and sleep tight.
        ZZZ_MMM_MUMBLE_MUMBLE_2                                                       = 8153,  -- Zzz... Mmm...<mumble-mumble>...
        HIYAA_A_POWER_PUNCH                                                           = 8154,  -- Hiyaa`a! Power punch!!!
        HEY_IS_THAT_THE_SAME_RIBBON_AS_BEFORE                                         = 8155,  -- Hey, is that the same ribbon as before? You mean it came back to you somehow?
        IS_IT_REALLY_ONE_AND_THE_SAME_PLEASE                                          = 8156,  -- Is it really one and the same? Please lend me this ribbon again for a little while.
        HUH_WHAT_DID_YOU_DO_WITH_THAT_DON                                             = 8157,  -- Huh...? What did you do with that %? Don't tell me you threw it away somewhere!
        WELL_IF_IT_HAPPENS_TO_COME_YOUR_WAY                                           = 8158,  -- Well, if it happens to come your way again, please bring it to me so I can check it. Cursed items are like boomerangs. They just keep on coming back!
        THERE_S_A_SUSPICIOUS_LOOKING_BOOK_HERE                                        = 8159,  -- There's a suspicious-looking book here...
        CHECK_ITS_CONTENTS_NO_WAY_TAKE_A_PEEK                                         = 8160,  -- Check its contents? No way! Take a peek.
        OH_NO_YOU_VE_BEEN_CURSED                                                      = 8161,  -- Oh, no! You've been cursed!
        OR_SO_YOU_THOUGHT_FOR_A_SECOND_THERE                                          = 8162,  -- ...or so you thought for a second there.
        THERE_S_A_THICK_BOOK_WITH_A_TITLE                                             = 8163,  -- There's a thick book with a title you can't make out.
        HAVE_A_QUICK_LOOK_INSIDE_NO_WAY_TAKE                                          = 8164,  -- Have a quick look inside. No way! Take a peek.
        WOW_YOU_RECEIVED_300_000_GIL                                                  = 8165,  -- Wow! You received 300,000 gil!
        OR_SO_YOU_THOUGHT_FOR_A_SECOND_THERE_2                                        = 8166,  -- ...or so you thought for a second there.
        YOU_HEAR_A_STRANGE_SOUND_IT_APPEARS_TO                                        = 8167,  -- You hear a strange sound... It appears to be coming from this book.
        CHECK_OUT_WHAT_S_INSIDE_NO_WAY_TAKE                                           = 8168,  -- Check out what's inside? No way! Take a peek.
        YOU_SIMPLY_CAN_T_OPEN_IT                                                      = 8169,  -- .........You simply can't open it!
        HRMM_HEY_YOU_WHAT_ARE_YOU_DOING_THERE                                         = 8170,  -- Hrmm. Hey you! What are you doing there?
        YOU_LOOK_LIKE_AN_ADVENTURER_OR_SOME_OTHER                                     = 8171,  -- You look like an adventurer or some other riff-raff. It doesn't seem like you'd have any business with our distinguished Library of Magic!
        HUAH_SAY_WHAT_THIS_IS_THE_LIBRARY_OF                                          = 8172,  -- Huah...? Say what...? This is the Library of Magic. If you make too much noise, we'll kick you out, so look around quietly!
        OH_AND_BE_WARNED_IF_LAYFOLK_SUCH_AS                                           = 8173,  -- Oh, and be warned. If layfolk such as you go around opening books at random, you could find yourself in more trouble than you bargained for. Huah...! ZZZzzz...
        SHH_CAN_T_YOU_SEE_I_M_IN                                                      = 8174,  -- Shh...! Can't you see I'm in the middle of transcribing this book here? Please keep your voice down!
        THIS_IS_THE_MANUSCRIPT_ROOM_THIS_IS_WHERE                                     = 8175,  -- This is the manuscript room. This is where we carry out the transcription of the library's older books into new books.
        THIS_COPYING_OF_MANUSCRIPTS_HAS_BEEN_REPEATED_FOR                             = 8176,  -- This copying of manuscripts has been repeated for hundreds of years. It is a work that never finishes.
        THE_BOOKS_IN_THIS_LIBRARY_OF_MAGIC_HAVE                                       = 8177,  -- The books in this Library of Magic have special spells cast on them.
        THOSE_SPELLS_ONLY_LAST_A_FEW_HUNDRED_YEARS                                    = 8178,  -- Those spells only last a few hundred years or so. That's why we recast them with new magic. If we don't, the knowledge found within these books will perish.
        ONE_OF_THESE_ANCIENT_MANUSCRIPTS_HAS_SUCH_EXTREMELY                           = 8179,  -- One of these ancient manuscripts has such extremely potent magic cast on it, it doesn't need to be transcribed over and over like this.
        THIS_MANUSCRIPT_IS_CALLED_THE_BOOK_OF_THE                                     = 8180,  -- This manuscript is called the Book of the Gods. It is a special book that only the Minister of the Optistery is allowed to handle.
        I_M_GOING_TO_READ_AS_MANY_BOOKS                                               = 8181,  -- I'm going to read as many books as I can. With all that knowledge, I can become valedictorian of the School of Magic!
        THEN_WHEN_I_GRADUATE_I_LL_ENTER_ONE                                           = 8182,  -- Then when I graduate, I'll enter one of the ministries, work my way up to minister, then become a professor when I retire.
        ADULTS_ARE_ALWAYS_TELLING_US_NOT_TO_SAY                                       = 8183,  -- Adults are always telling us not to say unchildish things. But we youths have to know the so-called workings of this world if we're going to survive.
        IF_YOU_GO_TOO_SLOW_YOU_LL_BE                                                  = 8184,  -- If you go too slow, you'll be left behind in this ever-changing world of ours.
        HRRRRM_THAT_CAN_T_BE_IT_THEN_AGAIN                                            = 8185,  -- Hrrrrm... That can't be it... Then again... Hr-hr-hr-hrmm...
        HRM_HEY_YOU_RE_THE_ADVENTURER_FROM_THE                                        = 8186,  -- Hrm! Hey, you're the adventurer from the other day! I don't believe it! I don't believe a word anyone says!
        HR_HR_HR_HRMM_THANKS_TO_SOME_ADVENTURER                                       = 8187,  -- Hr-hr-hr-hrmm... Thanks to some adventurer somewhere, I was able to awaken from an inescapable nightmare.
        THE_RESURRECTION_OF_THE_SHADOW_LORD_AND_THE                                   = 8188,  -- The resurrection of the Shadow Lord and the Book of the Gods losing its magic... Those things couldn't possibly happen. It was all but a dream...
        SHH_CAN_T_YOU_SEE_I_M_IN_2                                                    = 8189,  -- Shh...! Can't you see I'm in the middle of transcribing this book here? Please keep your voice down!
        HERETOFORE_SOURCE_OF_MAGICK_PRIMARILY_EXTRINSIC_ENERGIES_FILL                 = 8190,  -- Heretofore, source of magick...primarily extrinsic energies...fill terra and caelum.
        TARUTARU_ANALYZED_EXTRINSIC_ENERGY_CLASSIFYING_INTO_EIGHT_ELEMENTS            = 8191,  -- Tarutaru...analyzed...extrinsic energy...classifying into eight...elements. These...give birth magick...resides in soul...woven into spells...both...er, both...
        WHAT_S_THIS_2                                                                 = 8192,  -- ...What's this?
        I_DON_T_KNOW_HOW_TO_READ_THIS                                                 = 8193,  -- I don't know how to read this glyph. That's the trouble with ancient writings; the letters and characters are too hard to read...
        HEY_YOU_THERE_YOU_WOULDN_T_HAPPEN_TO                                          = 8194,  -- Hey, you there! You wouldn't happen to be passing through West Sarutabaruta anytime soon, would you? If so, I have a little favor to ask...
        LISTEN_TO_HARIGA_ORIGA_S_REQUEST_LISTEN_DON                                   = 8195,  -- Listen to Hariga-Origa's request? Listen. Don't listen.
        WELL_I_GUESS_IT_CAN_T_BE_HELPED                                               = 8196,  -- Well, I guess it can't be helped then... I'll just have to give up until someone can go there for me.
        ONE_OF_OUR_RESEARCHERS_JUST_HEADED_OFF_TO                                     = 8197,  -- One of our researchers just headed off to the Horutoto Ruins in West Sarutabaruta.
        SHE_SPECIALIZES_IN_PALEOGRAPHY_SO_SHE_SHOULD_BE                               = 8198,  -- She specializes in paleography, so she should be able to read these glyphs with no trouble at all.
        COULD_YOU_DO_ME_A_FAVOR_AND_PASS                                              = 8199,  -- Could you do me a favor and pass her this memo? Her name is Ipupu.
        HURRY_UP_AND_PASS_THAT_MEMO_TO_IPUPU                                          = 8200,  -- Hurry up and pass that memo to Ipupu. She's in West Sarutabaruta, probably in one of the magic towers of the Horutoto Ruins.
        UNTIL_I_CAN_READ_THE_GLYPH_I_WROTE                                            = 8201,  -- Until I can read the glyph I wrote in that memo, I have to give up... But I can't rest now, as I have so many other books to do. Guess I'll just have to get on with them in the meantime.
        THE_TRANSCRIPTION_OF_THESE_MANUSCRIPTS_IS_SO_BOTHERSOME                       = 8202,  -- The transcription of these manuscripts is so bothersome. It's impossible to read the ancient letters, and if you make a little mistake in their pronunciation, BOOM! The whole book goes and explodes in your face.
        BUT_IF_YOU_AVOID_THE_OLD_BOOKS_YOU                                            = 8203,  -- But if you avoid the old books, you'll only have more trouble when it comes to reading the ancient writings. You just can't win.
        LATELY_IPUPU_HAS_BEEN_TRANSCRIBING_SOME_ANCIENT_SCROLLS                       = 8204,  -- Lately Ipupu has been transcribing some ancient scrolls regarding the Horutoto Ruins.
        SO_MY_GUESS_IS_THAT_SHE_S_HEADED                                              = 8205,  -- So my guess is that she's headed for the central tower of the Horutoto Ruins.
        OH_WELCOME_BACK_WERE_YOU_ABLE_TO_GET                                          = 8206,  -- Oh, welcome back. Were you able to get any feedback from Ipupu?
        HU_HUM_SO_THIS_GLYPH_JUST_HAS_THE                                             = 8207,  -- Hu-hum... So, this glyph just has the meaning of sanative? Why didn't they just write healing, for crying out loud? Anyway, so where was I...
        HERETOFORE_THE_SOURCE_OF_MAGICK_WAS_PRIMARILY_THE                             = 8208,  -- Heretofore, the source of magick was primarily the extrinsic energies that fill terra and caelum.
        THE_TARUTARU_HAD_ANALYZED_THAT_EXTRINSIC_ENERGY_CLASSIFYING                   = 8209,  -- The Tarutaru had analyzed that extrinsic energy, classifying it into eight elements. These elements give birth to magick that resides in the soul to be woven into spells both sanative and hostile.
        HOWEVER_AFTER_MANY_LONG_YEARS_OF_STUDY_THE                                    = 8210,  -- However, after many long years of study, the existence of a converse of extrinsic energy, intrinsic energy from the soul itself, was discovered.
        PHEW_THIS_BOOK_IS_WAY_TOO_COMPLICATED_I                                       = 8211,  -- Phew! This book is way too complicated. I think I'll leave it here for today...
        OH_THAT_S_RIGHT_I_HAD_BETTER_REWARD                                           = 8212,  -- Oh, that's right, I had better reward you with something for helping me out there. Let me see... How about this map I have here? I'm sure you'll find this useful in your adventures!
        LET_ME_SEE_WHAT_WAS_THAT_BOOK_ABOUT                                           = 8213,  -- Let me see... What was that book about? Something to do with extrinsic energy and the soul's own intrinsic energy...?
        THAT_REMINDS_ME_OF_SOMETHING_I_HEARD_IN                                       = 8214,  -- That reminds me of something I heard in one of my lessons at the School of Magic... Magic from the heart that uses the soul's energy is what gave birth to magic dolls and automaton guards.
        HRMM_HEY_YOU_WHAT_ARE_YOU_DOING_THERE_2                                       = 8215,  -- Hrmm. Hey you! What are you doing there?
        HRMM_JUST_A_SECOND_I_COULD_USE_YOU                                            = 8216,  -- Hrmm!? Just a second... I could use you. Would you be willing to do a little chore for me in return for some money?
        TAKE_ON_THE_CHORE_ACCEPT_DECLINE                                              = 8217,  -- Take on the chore? Accept. Decline.
        YOU_DON_T_NEED_THE_CASH_HAH_JUST                                              = 8218,  -- You don't need the cash? Hah! Just goes to show you can't judge a book by its cover, then... Anyway, I'm busy, so off with you!
        GOOD_FIRST_LET_ME_EXPLAIN_A_BIT_ABOUT                                         = 8219,  -- Good! First, let me explain a bit about our distinguished library.
        WHA_WHA_WHA_WHAT_YOU_DON_T_NEED                                               = 8220,  -- Wha-wha-wha-what??? You don't need me to tell you? You already know? Hr-hr-hr-hrmm...
        THIS_LIBRARY_S_OFFICIAL_NAME_IS_THE_FEDERAL                                   = 8221,  -- This library's official name is the Federal Book Repository for Magical Knowledge and Research...
        ALSO_KNOWN_AS_THE_BOOK_REPOSITORY_OF_GENERAL                                  = 8222,  -- Also known as the Book Repository of General Knowledges. It is under the jurisdiction of the Optistery, the ministry that forbids the loss of knowledge.
        UNDER_THE_STRICT_SUPERVISION_OF_SUCCESSIVE_MINISTERS_OUR                      = 8223,  -- Under the strict supervision of successive ministers, our Optistery has protected the knowledge stored here with a system that doesn't allow even a baby ant to go unaccounted for.
        FOR_INSTANCE_THE_DIARY_THAT_DISAPPEARS_INTO_BLANK                             = 8224,  -- For instance, the diary that disappears into blank pages after three days, or the housekeeping account book that's so red, it makes your eyes weep.
        ONCE_A_BOOK_OR_SCROLL_IS_PLACED_IN                                            = 8225,  -- Once a book or scroll is placed in our care, we will never allow its content to be lost.
