        HEE_HEE_SHOPPING_IS_GREAT_FUN_BUT_BE                                          = 8665,  -- Hee-hee. Shopping is great fun, but be careful not to waste money on things you don't really need.
        IF_YOU_NEED_TO_KNOW_MORE_JUST_ASK                                             = 8666,  -- If you need to know more, just ask our friend, Jack of Hearts. He's on patrol near the Huntsman's Court.
        HERE_IF_YOU_GIVE_JACKY_WACKY_THIS_I                                           = 8667,  -- Here. If you give Jacky-wacky this, I'm sure he'll reward you somehow. To pass him the item, target him and select Trade from the main menu.
        I_HOPE_WE_MEET_AGAIN_SOON_GOOD_LUCK_2                                         = 8668,  -- I hope we meet again soon. Good luck, my new adventurer friend!
        PHEW_IMPOSSIBLE_TO_GET_A_WORD_IN_EDGEWISE                                     = 8669,  -- ...Phew! Impossible to get a word in edgewise, isn't it? She may be my little sister, but I don't understand her at all.
        WELL_I_D_BEST_BE_OFF_TOO_SEE                                                  = 8670,  -- Well, I'd best be off, too. See you around, I suppose. Ta-taru!
        DUH_THAT_S_EASY_WEASY_JUST_WALK_AROUND                                        = 8671,  -- Duh! That's easy-weasy. Just walk around the whole town and talk to anybody and everybody.
        OH_AJIDO_MARUJIDO_BITE_YOUR_TONGUE                                            = 8672,  -- Oh, Ajido-Marujido!!! Bite your tongue!
        LET_ME_SEE_I_CAN_TELL_YOU_ALL                                                 = 8673,  -- Let me see... I can tell you all the helpful information I know. Anything in particular you're interested in?
        ASK_ABOUT_HELPING_PEOPLE_MONSTER_PATROL_EASY_MONEY                            = 8674,  -- Ask about...? Helping people. Monster patrol. Easy money. Looking for work.
        IF_YOU_RE_VOLUNTEERING_TO_HELP_THEN_PLEASE                                    = 8675,  -- If you're volunteering to help, then please come to my ministry. It's called the Manustery, and is located in Windurst Woods. That's the district southeast of here.
        MY_MEMBERS_AND_I_WILL_TELL_YOU_THE                                            = 8676,  -- My members and I will tell you the details when you turn up. We'd be most appreciative of an extra hand.
        HUMPH_WATCH_OUT_IF_YOU_RE_GOING_TO                                            = 8677,  -- Humph. Watch out if you're going to deal with her. She loves to boss people around. Especially new arrivals like yourself.
        HOW_DARE_YOU_AJIDO_MARUJIDO_WHY_DON_T                                         = 8678,  -- How dare you, Ajido-Marujido! Why don't you shut your mouth!
        ANYWAY_IF_YOU_GET_STUCK_OR_DON_T                                              = 8679,  -- Anyway, if you get stuck or don't know what to do, try asking other adventurers for advice.
        ONLY_MY_BROTHER_IS_SUCH_A_NASTY_LYING                                         = 8680,  -- Only my brother is such a nasty, lying fiend. The rest of the people should be comparatively nicer.
        WHAT_DID_YOU_CALL_ME_THAT_S_RICH                                              = 8681,  -- What did you call me!? That's rich, coming from fuddy-duddy, hoity-toity, you! Don't forget who's been looking after you all these years!
        WELL_I_NEVER_I_DON_T_HAVE_THE                                                 = 8682,  -- Well, I never! I don't have the time for this nonsense. I'm off!
        HE_Y_WAIT_UP_AJIDO_MARUJIDO                                                   = 8683,  -- He`y! Wait up, Ajido-Marujido!
        SORRY_BUT_I_HAVE_TO_GO_TOO_IF_2                                               = 8684,  -- Sorry, but I have to go, too. If you need to know more, ask our friend Jack of Hearts who is on patrol near the Huntsman's Court.
        HERE_IF_YOU_GIVE_JACKY_WACKY_THIS_I_2                                         = 8685,  -- Here. If you give Jacky-wacky this, I'm sure he'll reward you somehow. To pass him the item, target him and select Trade from the main menu.
        BYE_BYE_AND_GOOD_LUCK_MY_NEW_ADVENTURER                                       = 8686,  -- Bye-bye, and good luck, my new adventurer friend! Please drop by my Manustery when you're in Windurst Woods.
        TSK_ADVENTURERS_THESE_DAYS_YOU_SHOULDN_T_GO                                   = 8687,  -- Tsk. Adventurers these days... You shouldn't go around saying that when it's your first time in a big city. You're sure to run into trouble.
        DON_T_BE_TOO_HARD_ON_NOVICE_ADVENTURERS                                       = 8688,  -- Don't be too hard on novice adventurers. I think it's only rational to first improve one's economic standing before setting out on a new adventuring enterprise.
        IN_FACT_I_THINK_I_KNOW_JUSTARU_THE                                            = 8689,  -- In fact, I think I know justaru the right person to help you out...
        OH_REALLY_WHO_WOULD_EVER_TELL_YOU_THAT                                        = 8690,  -- Oh, really? Who would ever tell you that they need help...?
        THE_HATTER_LATELY_HE_S_BEEN_CALLING_OUT                                       = 8691,  -- The hatter! Lately he's been calling out to my students, telling them that he'll give them some pocket money if they help him show off his wares.
        I_D_SAY_THAT_THE_SHAPE_OF_YOUR                                                = 8692,  -- I'd say that the shape of your head isn't too displeasing, so you might be able to earn some money...
        WELL_IF_YOU_COUNT_THAT_TYPE_OF_JOB                                            = 8693,  -- Well, if you count that type of job as easy then, yes, it could be considered easy money, but...
        SEE_THEN_IT_S_UP_TO_HOW_WELL                                                  = 8694,  -- ...See, then it's up to how well our friend performs. The more effort one puts in, the more one will earn!
        I_GUESS_SO_WELL_GOOD_LUCK_WITH_IT                                             = 8695,  -- I guess so. Well, good luck with it! I hope to see you again soon.
        IF_YOU_NEED_TO_KNOW_MORE_ASK_OUR                                              = 8696,  -- If you need to know more, ask our friend, Jack of Hearts. He's on patrol near the Huntsman's Court.
        HERE_IF_YOU_GIVE_JACKY_WACKY_THIS_I_3                                         = 8697,  -- Here. If you give Jacky-wacky this, I'm sure he'll reward you somehow. To pass him the item, target him and select Trade from the main menu.
        THE_DHALMEL_FARMER_UP_NEAR_THE_MANUSTERY_SEEMS                                = 8698,  -- The dhalmel farmer up near the Manustery seems to be having a pest problem. She's been asking for help in reducing the number of Crawlers in these parts.
        SPEAK_TO_ILLU_BOHJAA_SHE_S_A_MITHRA                                           = 8699,  -- Speak to Illu Bohjaa. She's a Mithra who looks after the dhalmels at the dhalmel farm in Windurst Woods.
        WINDURST_WOODS_IS_THE_SOUTHEASTERN_DISTRICT_OF_WINDURST                       = 8700,  -- Windurst Woods is the southeastern district of Windurst. Follow that little road eastwards, through Windurst Walls, on to the Woods district.
        IT_S_QUITE_A_DISTANCE_FROM_WINDURST_WATERS                                    = 8701,  -- It's quite a distance from Windurst Waters, but those dhalmels have such long necks, you should be able to spot them from a malm away.
        I_HATE_THAT_PLACE_WINDURST_WOODS_IS_ALL                                       = 8702,  -- I hate that place. Windurst Woods is all so higgledy-piggledy, I get lost every time I try to walk through it.
        REALLY_IF_YOU_JUST_FOLLOW_THE_PATH_AROUND                                     = 8703,  -- Really? If you just follow the path around, you'll find the dhalmel farm and Manustery relatively easily.
        BUT_I_DON_T_GO_TO_THOSE_PLACES                                                = 8704,  -- But I don't go to those places. I usually go to... ...... ............
        OH_NO_I_TOTALLY_FORGOTARU_I_SHOULD_BE                                         = 8705,  -- Oh, no! I totally forgotaru! I should be preparing for my experiment. Sorry. I've got to run!
        OH_BROTHER_WOTHER_WHAT_EVIL_SCHEME_ARE_YOU                                    = 8706,  -- Oh brother-wother! What evil scheme are you up to now? Hold on a second!
        IF_YOU_NEED_TO_KNOW_MORE_ASK_OUR_2                                            = 8707,  -- If you need to know more, ask our friend, Jack of Hearts. He's on patrol near the Huntsman's Court.
        HERE_IF_YOU_GIVE_JACKY_WACKY_THIS_I_4                                         = 8708,  -- Here. If you give Jacky-wacky this, I'm sure he'll reward you somehow. To pass him the item, target him and select Trade from the main menu.
        GOOD_LUCK_I_HOPE_WE_MEET_AGAIN_SOON                                           = 8709,  -- Good luck! I hope we meet again, soon. Ta-taru!
        THAT_S_EASY_IF_YOU_RE_LOOKING_FOR                                             = 8710,  -- That's easy. If you're looking for work, then head on over to one of the gatehouses.
        FOLLOW_THAT_ROAD_BEHIND_YOU_AND_IT_LL                                         = 8711,  -- Follow that road behind you and it'll lead you to a big stone building. That's the north gatehouse.
        GATEHOUSES_ARE_SPECIAL_PLACES_THAT_HAND_OUT_MISSIONS                          = 8712,  -- Gatehouses are special places that hand out missions on behalf of the Federation of Windurst.
        WHEN_YOU_SUCCESSFULLY_COMPLETE_MISSIONS_OBTAINED_FROM_THE                     = 8713,  -- When you successfully complete missions obtained from the gatehouses, the town guards will increase your rank points.
        COLLECT_ENOUGH_RANK_POINTS_AND_YOUR_RANK_OR_2                                 = 8714,  -- Collect enough rank points and your rank, or position within this country, will rise.
        OH_AND_YOU_RE_CURRENTLY_RANK_ONE_BY                                           = 8715,  -- Oh, and you're currently rank one, by the way.
        IN_OTHER_WORDS_YOU_RE_THE_LOWEST_OF                                           = 8716,  -- In other words, you're the lowest of the low, the weakest of the weak...
        PAY_NO_ATTENTION_TO_MY_BROTHER                                                = 8717,  -- ...Pay no attention to my brother.
        YOU_CAN_ONLY_ACCEPT_ONE_MISSION_AT_A                                          = 8718,  -- You can only accept one mission at a time, but if you do each one properly, your rank is sure to go up in no time at all.
        YEAH_AND_THEN_YOU_LL_BE_SECOND_LOWEST                                         = 8719,  -- Yeah, and then you'll be second-lowest of the low, the second most weakest of the weak...
        OH_SHUT_UP_ALREADY                                                            = 8720,  -- Oh, shut up already!
        MISSIONS_ARE_DONE_FOR_THE_LOVE_OF_YOUR                                        = 8721,  -- Missions are done for the love of your country, so don't expect to make much money out of them. But give them your best shot! Not all rewards can be measured in gil.
        AS_YOU_INCREASE_IN_RANK_YOU_CAN_GAIN                                          = 8722,  -- As you increase in rank, you can gain better things than gil can buy.
        YEAH_IF_YOUR_RANK_GOES_UP_ENOUGH_YOU                                          = 8723,  -- Yeah, if your rank goes up enough, you might even be able to talk to us on equal footing.
        IF_YOU_NEED_TO_KNOW_ANYTHING_ELSE_ASK                                         = 8724,  -- If you need to know anything else, ask our friend, Jack of Hearts. He's on patrol near the Huntsman's Court.
        HERE_IF_YOU_GIVE_OLD_JACK_THIS_I                                              = 8725,  -- Here. If you give old Jack this, I'm sure he'll reward you. To pass him it, target him and select Trade from the main menu.
        THAT_S_ALL_THE_HELP_I_CAN_GIVE                                                = 8726,  -- That's all the help I can give you for now. Well, see you around, newbie.
        AH_WAIT_UP_AJIDO_MARUJIDO                                                     = 8727,  -- Ah! Wait up, Ajido-Marujido.
        MY_BROTHER_ALWAYS_DOES_THINGS_HIS_OWN_WAY                                     = 8728,  -- My brother always does things his own way, regardless of others.
        GOOD_LUCK_ADVENTURER_HOPE_TO_SEE_YOU_AROUND                                   = 8729,  -- Good luck, adventurer! Hope to see you around someday. Bye-bye!
        THIS_IS_TARUTARU_WE_ARE_WINDURST_YOU_ARE                                      = 8730,  -- This is Tarutaru. We are Windurst. You are our new slave...
        OH_AJIDO_MARUJIDO_BITE_YOUR_TONGUE_2                                          = 8731,  -- Oh, Ajido-Marujido!!! Bite your tongue!
        THIS_PLACE_IS_CALLED_WINDURST_WATERS_IT_IS                                    = 8732,  -- This place is called Windurst Waters. It is the oldest of the four districts of Windurst, and has been the center of Tarutaru life for ages.
        IN_WINDURST_THERE_ARE_FIVE_EDUCATIONAL_AND_GOVERNMENTAL                       = 8733,  -- In Windurst, there are five educational and governmental ministries. The ministers themselves support the Star Sibyl, who rules over Windurst.
        THREE_OF_THE_MINISTRIES_ARE_HERE_IN_WINDURST                                  = 8734,  -- Three of the ministries are here in Windurst Waters. Many Tarutaru are involved in studying a variety of subjects at these institutions.
        THESE_THREE_MINISTRIES_ARE_KNOWN_AS_THE_OPTISTERY                             = 8735,  -- These three ministries are known as the Optistery, Rhinostery, and Aurastery. Respectively, they administrate a library, biological laboratory, and magic school.
        YOU_LL_ALSO_FIND_SEVERAL_TARUTARU_RUN_SHOPS                                   = 8736,  -- You'll also find several Tarutaru-run shops in this area.
        THERE_S_A_HOSTELRY_A_GENERAL_GOODS_STORE                                      = 8737,  -- There's a hostelry, a general goods store, a milliner...oh, and the Culinarians' Guild, and the tavern... It will take you more than a day to see all the sights.
        AH_AND_ONE_SHOULDN_T_FORGET_THE_RESIDENTIAL                                   = 8738,  -- Ah, and one shouldn't forget the residential area. Follow the little road that leads to Windurst Walls and turn right to find the entrance.
        IN_WINDURST_S_RESIDENTIAL_AREA_THERE_IS_A                                     = 8739,  -- In Windurst's residential area, there is a Mog House for you to store items and rest up in. Talk to the guards at the entranceway for the details.
        UMMM_WHAT_ELSE_WERE_YOU_ASKING_ABOUTARU                                       = 8740,  -- Ummm... What else were you asking aboutaru...?
        HUH_OH_YEAH_JUST_WHO_IN_VANA_DIEL                                             = 8741,  -- Huh? Oh yeah, just who in Vana'diel are we...!?
        HEE_HEE_WELL_IF_YOU_HAVEN_T_FIGURED                                           = 8742,  -- Hee-hee. Well, if you haven't figured it out already, I'm Apururu. Nice to meetaru you.t
        OH_YEAH_AND_I_M_AJIDO_MARUJIDO_IT                                             = 8743,  -- Oh, yeah, and I'm Ajido-Marujido. It'll pay to remember me.
        WELL_I_GUESS_YOU_STILL_HAVE_PLENTY_OF                                         = 8744,  -- Well, I guess you still have plenty of questions to ask, but we have to get going now.
        I_SUGGEST_YOU_ASK_YOUR_FELLOW_ADVENTURERS_FOR                                 = 8745,  -- I suggest you ask your fellow adventurers for help. Vana'diel is a huge place, so you'll need to make as many friends as you can.
        HAH_FRIENDS_I_HAD_BETTER_WARN_YOU_DON                                         = 8746,  -- Hah! Friends... I had better warn you...don't go around telling people you're my friend, rightaru?
        AH_AJIDO_MARUJIDO_WAIT_UP_A_MOMENT                                            = 8747,  -- Ah, Ajido-Marujido! Wait up a moment!
        OH_BEFORE_I_GO_HERE_TAKE_THIS_GIVE                                            = 8748,  -- Oh, before I go, here, take this. Give it to our friend, Jack of Hearts, who is on patrol near the Huntsman's Court.
        JACKY_WACKY_IS_A_GOOD_LITTLE_CARDIAN_WHO                                      = 8749,  -- Jacky-wacky is a good little Cardian who will tell you anything else you need to know. To pass him the coupon, target him and select Trade from the main menu.
        I_HOPE_TO_SEE_YOU_AROUND_SOME_TIME                                            = 8750,  -- I hope to see you around some time. Good luck, my shiny-whiny adventurer friend. Ta-taru!t
        WHAT_S_THAT_A_TAT_TAT_PRINCIPAL_KORU                                          = 8751,  -- What's that, a-tat-tat? Principal Koru-Moru is secretly searching for something special?
        A_BURNITE_SHELL_WELL_OH_WELL_SAY_IF                                           = 8752,  -- A burnite shell...? Well, oh well...! Say, if it's shells you're seeking, your should speak to a son of the sea.
        A_BOOK_ON_ALCHEMY_EH_I_D_LOVE                                                 = 8753,  -- A book on Alchemy, eh? I'd love to take a look at one myself, I say. But they were all banned years ago. 'Twas said that they were a bad influence on children, you know?
        I_M_NOT_CERTAIN_WHETHER_THEY_REALLY_WERE                                      = 8754,  -- I'm not certain whether they really were or not. All I do know is--if I haven't forgot-- that getting your hands on one now will be close to impossible, I avow!
        PRINCIPAL_KORU_MORU_IS_SEARCHING_FOR_A_SCHOLAR                                = 8755,  -- Principal Koru-Moru is searching for a scholar knowledgeable in the art of Alchemy, eh? Still the dilly-dallier, I see...
        I_WONDER_IF_HE_S_SERIOUSLY_CONSIDERING_STUDYING                               = 8756,  -- I wonder if he's seriously considering studying something so sinister as Alchemy? If so, he's not setting a good example for his students, is he, eh?
        ALCHEMICAL_ALCHEMY_NOW_THAT_YOU_MENTION_IT_EVER                               = 8757,  -- Alchemical Alchemy? Now that you mention it, ever so long ago, a student wrote a graduation thesis on such a dubiously dubious topic...
        IF_I_REMEMBERINGLY_REMEMBER_THE_PRINCIPAL_AT_THE                              = 8758,  -- If I rememberingly remember, the principal at the time orderly ordered that student to stay back another year.
        WHAT_YOU_WANTINGLY_WANT_TO_READ_THAT_STUDENT                                  = 8759,  -- What? You wantingly want to read that student's graduation thesis?
        IT_SHOULDN_T_BE_A_PROBLEMATIC_PROBLEM_ASK                                     = 8760,  -- It shouldn't be a problematic problem... Ask Katzun-Nattzun at the Acolyte Hostel to help find it for you.
        THE_HOSTEL_IS_THE_HUMONGOUSLY_HUGE_BUILDING_TO                                = 8761,  -- The hostel is the humongously huge building to the north of here.
        GRADUATION_THESES_ARE_TESTS_TO_INDICATINGLY_INDICATE_WHETHER                  = 8762,  -- Graduation theses are tests to indicatingly indicate whether the students are able to graduate from the School of Magic.
        KATZUN_NATTZUN_SHOULD_KNOWINGLY_KNOW_WHERE_THAT_THESIS                        = 8763,  -- Katzun-Nattzun should knowingly know where that thesis is. You'll find him in the Acolyte Hostel, a humongously huge building to the north of here.
        WHAT_A_FINE_SAILOR_S_CAP_SUCH_A                                               = 8766,  -- What a fine sailor's cap... Such a shame it's so terribly torn...
        AND_THESE_ARE_MADE_OUT_OF_LEATHER_TOO                                         = 8767,  -- And these are made out of leather, too... It would be a damn sight quicker to make a new one.
        TO_HO_HO_MIGHT_AS_WELL_TRY_FULL                                               = 8768,  -- To-ho-ho... Might as well try full-scale surgery to see if we can resurrect the poor blighter.
        LISTEN_UP_I_LL_NEED_FOUR_TO_SAVE                                              = 8769,  -- Listen up. I'll need four % to save this worn and torn sailor...and a little bit of luck as well.
        TO_HO_HO_MIGHT_AS_WELL_TRY_FULL_2                                             = 8770,  -- To-ho-ho... Might as well try full-scale surgery to see if we can resurrect the poor blighter.
        LISTEN_UP_I_LL_NEED_FOUR_TO_SAVE_2                                            = 8771,  -- Listen up. I'll need four % to save this worn and torn sailor...and a little luck as well.
        WISH_ME_LUCK_CAUSE_HERE_IT_GOES                                               = 8772,  -- Wish me luck, 'cause here it goes...
        TA_DA_T_THE_OPERATION_WAS_A_SUCCESS                                           = 8773,  -- Ta`da`t The operation was a success! To tell you the truth, I had been working on it using some of the leather I had lying around here. To-ho-ho.
        OH_AND_HERE_I_ALSO_MADE_A_LITTLE                                              = 8774,  -- Oh, and here, I also made a little something for you, too...
        TO_HO_HO_I_JUST_MADE_IT_USING                                                 = 8775,  -- To-ho-ho! I just made it using the scraps of leather I had left over, but it's quite a dandy little design, isn't it?
        TO_HO_HO_NOT_THAT_IT_WOULD_HAPPEN                                             = 8776,  -- To-ho-ho! Not that it would happen, but if you ever lost your % again, just bring me four %, and I'll make you a new one.
        TO_DISGUISE_YOURSELF_WITH_DEARIE_OH_LIKE_DETECTIVE                            = 8777,  -- % to disguise yourself with, dearie? Oh...like Detective Poiroto-Boiroto in those Agatha Crystalie mystery series?
        OH_MY_DAUGHTER_PUT_YOU_UP_TO_THIS                                             = 8778,  -- Oh, my daughter put you up to this? Well then, I guess it can't be helped...
        IF_YOU_CAN_COLLECT_FOUR_LUMPS_OF_THE                                          = 8779,  -- If you can collect four lumps of the fluffy cotton wool that the monsters in Tahrongi Canyon drop, I'll try and make you one.
        THIS_SHOULD_BE_ENOUGH_HAIR_NOSE_OOPS_I                                        = 8780,  -- This should be enough. Hair nose, oops, I mean... Here goes...
        IN_THE_BOOKS_DETECTIVE_POIROTO_BOIROTO_COULD_CHANGE                           = 8781,  -- In the books, Detective Poiroto-Boiroto could change his appearance in a blink of the eye. That's why he's also known as the Mastaru of Disguise!
        ISN_T_HE_THE_MOSTEST                                                          = 8782,  -- Isn't he the mostest!?
        A_WHILE_AGO_I_BORROWED_A_CHOCOBO_SO                                           = 8783,  -- A while ago, I borrowed a chocobo so I could go on a fishing trip. But zee silly chocobo went and caught a cold.
        TO_MAKE_UP_FOR_EET_I_TOOK_SOME                                                = 8784,  -- To make up for eet, I took some of my special stew to zee stables so zee chocobo could drink eet... Oh, so you want moi to make some of zat stew for you?
        I_THINK_IT_EEZ_POSSIBLE_BUT_ZEE_SPECIAL                                       = 8785,  -- I think it eez possible, but zee special stew I made that time had % in eet. You'll have to bring moi three of zose little champignons...
        WITHOUT_ZOSE_SPECIAL_MUSHROOMS_EET_WILL_JUST_BE                               = 8786,  -- Without zose special mushrooms, eet will just be a plain old stew.
        ZEE_CAN_BE_FOUND_IN_JUGNER_FOREST_I                                           = 8787,  -- Zee % can be found in Jugner Forest, I believe.
        ZEY_GROW_ON_ZEE_BODIES_OF_ZEE_TOADSTOOL                                       = 8788,  -- Zey grow on zee bodies of zee toadstool monsters that lurk zere. Zey look grotesque and smell awful, but zee taste ees just exquisite!
        I_NEED_ABOUT_THREE_IN_ORDER_TO_MAKE                                           = 8789,  -- I need about three % in order to make zat special stew for you.
        IN_ORDER_TO_GET_ZOSE_MUSHROOMS_I_RECOMMEND                                    = 8790,  -- In order to get zose mushrooms, I recommend you try Jugner Forest. You should be able to collect zem by defeating zose toadstool monsters zat lurk zere.
        ZAT_S_IT_ONCE_YOU_VE_TRIED_A                                                  = 8791,  -- Zat's it! Once you've tried a dish with zese in zem, you'll keep coming back for more.
        ONE_MOMENT_PLEEZE_I_LL_ADD_A_LEETTLE                                          = 8792,  -- One moment pleeze. I'll add a leettle of zis and a leettle of zis and...
        VOIL_ZIS_SHOULD_GET_ZAT_CHOCOBO_BACK_ON                                       = 8793,  -- Voil%`! Zis should get zat chocobo back on his feet again!
        MAKE_SURE_YOU_BRING_EET_TO_HEEM_WHILE                                         = 8794,  -- Make sure you bring eet to heem while eet's still warm.
        ZAT_SHOULD_GET_OUR_CHOCOBO_FRIEND_BACK_ON                                     = 8795,  -- Zat should get our chocobo friend back on his feet again!
        MAKE_SURE_YOU_SERVE_IT_TO_HEEM_WHILE                                          = 8796,  -- Make sure you serve it to heem while eet's still warm.
        I_M_SURE_YOU_VE_HEARD_BY_NOW                                                  = 8797,  -- I'm sure you've heard by now that there are five ministries in Windurst, haven'taru?
        THIS_BUILDING_HOUSES_ONE_OF_THOSE_MINISTRIES_THE                              = 8798,  -- This building houses one of those ministries, the Optistery, which runs a Library of Magic. For ages, they have been in chargey-wargey of the preservation of Windurst's books and scrolls.
        WELCOME_TO_THE_MAGICAL_CITY_OF_WINDURST_HAVE                                  = 8799,  -- Welcome to the magical city of Windurst! Have you checked out the whole town yetaru? What's that...? You're having trouble talking with us Tarutaru?
        WELL_WE_MAY_BE_SMALL_AND_SPEAK_A                                              = 8800,  -- Well, we may be small and speak a little funny-wunny, but we're the best when it comes to using magic! If you have time, you should stop by the School of Magic and see how we learny-wearny!
        THE_RESEARCH_OF_MAGIC_IS_MALMS_AHEAD_IN                                       = 8801,  -- The research of magic is malms ahead in Windurst compared to the other countries. That's because the land in these parts was originally overflowing with magical power-wower.
        IN_SARUTABARUTA_THE_LAND_THAT_SURROUNDS_WINDURST_YOU                          = 8802,  -- In Sarutabaruta, the land that surrounds Windurst, you'll find the Horutoto Ruins. They're incredibly ancient remnants from a sorcerous society!
        DON_TARU_YOU_THINK_THE_WORLD_S_BECOME                                         = 8803,  -- Don'taru you think the world's become all so rowdy-dowdy lately? The Manustery making Cardians like there's no tomorrow... The Orastery has gone and allowed the sale of high-level magic...
        A_GUY_S_GOT_TO_THINK_OF_AN                                                    = 8804,  -- A guy's got to think of an escape plan in case the whole place gets pulled into a war or something.
        AHAHA_YOU_RE_SUCH_A_WORRYWART_THERE_WON                                       = 8805,  -- Ahaha... You're such a worrywart. There won't be another war!
        SO_LONG_AS_THE_STAR_SIBYL_BLESSES_US                                          = 8806,  -- So long as the Star Sibyl blesses us with her presence, the peace of Windurst is a given.
        I_VE_COME_HERE_TO_RETURN_THE_BOOK                                             = 8807,  -- I've come here to return the book I borrowed-worrowed from the Optistery's library. I'd really like to have kept it out a little longer, but...
        SEE_YOU_HAVE_TO_RETURN_IT_BACK_BY                                             = 8808,  -- See, you have to return it back by the due date. If you don't, the magic placed on the books can fadey-wadey, and all the letters in the book will vanish in an instant!
        DO_YOU_KNOW_OF_THEM_BEASTYMENS_THEM_BE                                        = 8809,  -- Do you know of them beastymens? Them be some smaaart monster-wonsters! They's attack peoples and steal peoples's stuff and all sorts of other nasty-wasty things.
        BUT_THEY_SAY_THEM_YAGUDO_AREN_T_BAAAD                                         = 8810,  -- But they say them Yagudo aren't baaad beastymens. Them not like them other beastymens, they says. But is it true-wrue...? I wonders!
        WHEN_MY_DADDY_WADDY_STILL_HAD_HIS_HEALTH                                      = 8811,  -- When my daddy-waddy still had his health, he fought them Yagudo. He says all four countries united their powers to defeat the king of the beastymens at a castle waay up northy-worthy. I wish I lived back then.
        EW_AN_INDESCRIBABLE_SMELL_OCCASIONALLY_COMES_WAFTING_ACROSS                   = 8812,  -- Ew! An indescribable smell occasionally comes wafting across from that building over yonder-wonder.
        THAT_S_THE_CULINARIANS_GUILD_ISN_T_IT                                         = 8813,  -- That's the Culinarians' Guild, isn't it? What in Vana'diel are they cooking-wooking in there?
        THAT_S_THE_CULI_CULIN_CULNIRA_COOKS_GUILD                                     = 8814,  -- That's the Culi...Culin...Culnira...Cooks' Guild! We's all likes Ranpi-Monpi who works there. He lets us taste all sortsa great stuff!
        HE_SEZ_I_VE_AN_IRON_CLAD_TUMMY                                                = 8815,  -- He sez I've an iron-clad tummy-wummy, so I comes in mighty useful!
        TNANAH_NANANAH_T_BEFORE_A_NEW_DISH_GETS                                       = 8816,  -- tNanah-nananah!t Before a new dish gets added to the menu at the westaurant over there, we's alweady tasted it! I bet you're jealous, 'coz we're sooo wucky!
        LET_KIDS_BE_KIDS_IS_WHAT_I_SAY                                                = 8817,  -- Let kids be kids is what I say. Even if they're mischievous and hate to study, it's fine, so long as they are sound and well.
        THOUGH_IT_WOULDN_T_HURT_FOR_THEM_TO                                           = 8818,  -- Though it wouldn't hurt for them to master a few magical techniques, just in case the Yagudo Theomilitary decides to bear their beaks like they did twenty years ago...
        MY_MOMMY_WOMMY_WORKS_IN_THAT_SHOPPY_WOPPY                                     = 8819,  -- My mommy-wommy works in that shoppy-woppy there! When you comes back from your twavels outside, you just gotta stop by there!
        WANT_TO_LEARN_HOW_TO_USE_A_LITTLE                                             = 8820,  -- Want to learn how to use a little magic? You should stop by the School of Magic, which is run by the Aurastery. It's across the bridge here and up to your left.
        OH_IT_S_PROBABLY_QUICKER_TO_ASK_THE                                           = 8821,  -- Oh... It's probably quicker to ask the students than the teachers. The educatees there are more eager scholars than the educators.
        HAVE_YOU_SEEN_THE_GREAT_STAR_TREE_THE                                         = 8822,  -- Have you seen the Great Star Tree, the symbol of Windurst's peace? In the old days, we celebrated a Festival of the Stars where the Star Sibyl made the tree suddenly bloom with nuts.
        IN_THE_GOOD_OLD_DAYS_IT_WAS_THE                                               = 8823,  -- In the good old days, it was the custom to hold a Festival of the Stars as a welcoming after the Star Reading ceremony.
        BUT_THAT_WAS_IN_THE_YEARS_BEFORE_THE                                          = 8824,  -- But that was in the years before the war... After an ill-omened fortune was told in the Star Reading ceremony, we stopped conducting the Festival of the Stars.
        ACROSS_THE_BRIDGE_TO_THE_SOUTH_OF_HERE                                        = 8825,  -- Across the bridge to the south of here is Baren-Moren's hat shop, and the Rhinostery with its biological laboratory.
        FURTHER_TO_THE_SOUTH_IS_WINDURST_S_PORT                                       = 8826,  -- Further to the south is Windurst's port area. Ah, how I'd love to have a new hat made! I could wear it as I set off on a trip across the open skies...
        AMONG_THE_GUARDS_OF_WINDURST_ARE_THE_AUTOMATONS                               = 8827,  -- Among the guards of Windurst are the automatons who speaky-weaky in the words of the stars.
        THEY_ARE_THE_CARDIANS_MAGICAL_PUPPET_LIKE_DOLLY                               = 8828,  -- They are the Cardians, magical puppet-like dolly-wollys that are made at the Manustery.
        ONCE_IN_SEVERAL_HUNDRED_YEARS_A_GREAT_WIZARD                                  = 8829,  -- Once in several hundred years, a great wizard is born out of the Tarutaru in Windurst. This wizard is so powerful, he is called the Mastermind of the Millenium.
        DECADES_AGO_A_CHILD_FORMIDABLE_ENOUGH_TO_CARRY                                = 8830,  -- Decades ago, a child formidable enough to carry that title graduated at the top of his class from the School of Magic. I'm sure you'll hear his name mentioned as the hero who saved Windurst.
        THE_HORUTOTO_RUINS_IN_SARUTABARUTA_ARE_ALSO_CALLED                            = 8831,  -- The Horutoto Ruins in Sarutabaruta are also called the magic towers, and are said to have the power to control the monsters of Sarutabaruta.
        BUT_THEY_WERE_DAMAGED_TERRIBLY_WERRIBLY_DURING_THE                            = 8832,  -- But they were damaged terribly-werribly during the war. Now, most of the magical gizmos in there don't work anymore.
        AHHH_IF_ONLY_THOSE_MAGIC_TOWERS_COULD_BE                                      = 8833,  -- Ahhh... If only those magic towers could be restored, the Sarutabaruta region could have peace once more.
        WITH_ALL_THE_POWERS_THAT_THE_ELITE_SCHOLARS                                   = 8834,  -- With all the powers that the elite scholars of Windurst have, you'd think we could repair the Horutoto Ruins right away. The engineering skills of the ancients must be more complicated than we think. It's most disappointing-wointing.
        BUT_SPEAKING_OF_SCHOLARS_I_WONDER_WHAT_HAPPENED                               = 8835,  -- But speaking of scholars, I wonder what happened to all the combat scholars that made up a large portion of the Federation's ranks during the Crystal War. It was rumored that there were more than a handful of suspicious characters among them.
        PLEASE_OH_PLEEE_EEEASE_CAN_TARU_YOU_BUY                                       = 8836,  -- Please, oh pleee`eeease. Can'taru you buy me just one more hat?
        I_NEED_ONE_FOR_DAYTIME_AND_ONE_FOR                                            = 8837,  -- I need one for daytime and one for nighttime. That means I need eight more hats!
        ENOUGH_IS_ENOUGH_ALREADY_WEDDY_EIGHT_HATS_ARE                                 = 8838,  -- Enough is enough, already-weddy! Eight hats are sufficientaru for all the days of the week.
        IN_THE_TARUTARU_ESTATES_AREA_HERE_THE_BIGGEST                                 = 8839,  -- In the Tarutaru estates area here, the biggest and grandest house is inhabited by a super-rich Tarutaru.
        BUT_HE_S_THE_PERFECT_PICTURE_WICTURE_OF                                       = 8840,  -- But he's the perfect picture-wicture of a miser. When you just walk by his house, he judgmentally glares down at you as if you are a pauper-wauper or something. I can't stand it!
        THIS_CERTAINLY_WERTAINLY_IS_THE_ROAD_TO_THE                                   = 8841,  -- This certainly-wertainly is the road to the School of Magic. But what business do you have there? Aren't you a little old to be applying for school?
        MY_DAUGHTER_S_IN_THE_SCHOOL_OF_MAGIC                                          = 8842,  -- My daughter's in the School of Magic. She spends her days working hard at her studies there.
        DOES_SHE_REALIZE_HER_DADDY_WADDY_IS_HERE                                      = 8843,  -- Does she realize her daddy-waddy is here on this hill every day worrying about her? Is she eating her lunchy-wunchy properly? Is she being teased by the class bully-wully?
        DAUGHTER_DEAREST_YOUR_DADDY_WADDY_S_HERE_CHEERING                             = 8844,  -- Daughter dearest! Your Daddy-waddy's here, cheering you on! You go girl! Woo-hoo!
        IN_THE_SCHOOL_OF_MAGIC_THERE_IS_AN                                            = 8845,  -- In the School of Magic, there is an advanced class for the smarty-warties and a beginners class for the mediocre students.
        WHAT_S_THAT_YOU_THINK_YOU_CAN_ENTER                                           = 8846,  -- What's that!? You think you can enter the advanced class, huh? Well, the last year had a Mithra pass the grade, so maybe even you could give it a try...?
        GRRR_I_DON_T_HAVE_ENOUGH_GIL_TO                                               = 8847,  -- Grrr... I don't have enough gil to buy anything worrrthwhile. Guess I've got to head back out to Sarrrutabarrruta and hunt some more rarrrabs.
        DOESN_T_SEEM_LIKE_THERRRE_S_ANY_GOOD                                          = 8848,  -- Doesn't seem like therrre's any good offerrrs for half-baked adventurrrerrrs like you and me. Betterrr off sticking to rabbiting forrr the time being.
        WHAT_WAS_IT_CALLED_AGAIN_YOU_KNOW_THE                                         = 8849,  -- What was it called again? You know, the grrreat, whopping whatchamacallit monsterrr that stopped appearrring, allowing old Windurst to returrrn to its peaceful state?
        BACK_IN_THE_OLD_DAYS_WHEN_THERRRE_WAS                                         = 8850,  -- Back in the old days, when therrre was a full moon, the Tarutaru would lock and barrr theirrr doorrrs, too afrrraid to even peek outside.
        AREN_T_YOU_AN_ADVENTURER_FROM_INSTEAD_OF                                      = 8851,  -- Aren't you an adventurer from [San d'Oria/Bastok]? Instead of staying in a hostelry, wouldn't it be cheaper for you to stay in a Rrrent-a-Rrroom in Windurst's rrresidential area?
        THE_RRRESIDENTIAL_AREA_IS_EAST_OF_HERE_CROSS                                  = 8852,  -- The rrresidential area is east of here. Cross the bridge there and turn rrright where the Cardian is on guard.
        HEY_AREN_T_YOU_A_WINDURSTIAN_INSTEAD_OF                                       = 8853,  -- Hey, aren't you a Windurstian? Instead of staying at a hostelry, why don't you use your Mog House in Windurst's rrresidential area? It's free, isn't it?
        THE_RRRESIDENTIAL_AREA_IS_EAST_OF_HERE_CROSS_2                                = 8854,  -- The rrresidential area is east of here. Cross the bridge there and turn rrright where the Cardian is on guard.
        THERRRE_S_A_STRRRANGE_LADY_STAYING_IN_THE                                     = 8855,  -- Therrre's a strrrange lady staying in the rrroom on the second floor of the hostelrrry. She's funny, even forrr a Hume!
        BUT_SHE_S_LOVED_BY_THE_TARRRUTARRRU_I                                         = 8856,  -- But she's loved by the Tarrrutarrru. I guess it's trrrue what they say about chocobos of a featherrr flocking togetherrr.
        AHH_MAYBE_JUST_MAYBE_SHE_COULD_BE_A                                           = 8857,  -- Ahh!? Maybe, just maybe...she could be a prrrincess underrr some wicked spell?
        THAT_BUILDING_THERRRE_IS_A_HAT_SHOP_OF                                        = 8858,  -- That building therrre is a hat shop, of all things. Don't you think it shows how carefrrree a rrrace those Tarutaru are to make such a whimsical business?
        HATS_ARRRE_TOTALLY_USELESS_GIVE_ME_A_PROPERRR                                 = 8859,  -- Hats arrre totally useless! Give me a properrr armorrr helmet any day!
        WHEN_I_LOOK_AT_THESE_FLOWERRRS_I_FEEL                                         = 8860,  -- When I look at these flowerrrs, I feel like having a drrrink. But then again, I feel like having a drrrink all of the time.
        IF_ONLY_I_HAD_SOME_FLUORO_FLORA_JUICE                                         = 8861,  -- If only I had some fluoro-flora juice. It's as bitterrr as uncooked gysahl greens, but the taste rrreminds me of home.
        THE_ORRRIGINAL_FLUORO_FLORA_SEEDS_ARE_FROM_THE                                = 8862,  -- The orrriginal fluoro-flora seeds are from the Mithra homeland, you see...
        HUH_SO_THIS_IS_THE_BIOLOGICAL_LABORRRATORY_THAT                               = 8863,  -- Huh... So this is the biological laborrratory that is rrrun by the Rhinostery, eh? Doesn't seem so exciting, rrreally...
        I_HEARRRD_THAT_THEY_CARRY_OUT_SOME_WEIRRRD                                    = 8864,  -- I hearrrd that they carry out some weirrrd experiments herrre. Do you know anything about that?
        THOSE_STRANGE_PLANTS_THAT_GLOW_IN_THE_DARK                                    = 8865,  -- Those strange plants that glow in the dark? They say that they make them in the Rhinostery.
        HOW_DO_YOU_MAKE_PLANTS_THAT_GLOW_WINDURST                                     = 8866,  -- How do you make plants that glow? Windurst is truly a land of wonders. Why, I heard rumors that during the Crystal War, the ministry spent a great deal of Federation funding on queer biotechnological experiments such as the development of sleep-inducing fruit and vegetables that would not spoil for years.
        THE_RESIDENTS_HERE_ARE_A_TIMID_PEOPLE_YET                                     = 8867,  -- The residents here are a timid people, yet they know very well the beauty of the night. I'm amazed that they can create such exquisite plants.
        PHEW_I_FINALLY_MADE_IT_SO_THIS_IS                                             = 8868,  -- Phew... I finally made it! So this is the city of Windurst...?
        I_HAD_A_NASTY_EXPERIENCE_WHEN_I_WAS                                           = 8869,  -- I had a nasty experience when I was attacked by those awful Yagudo out there in Sarutabaruta. All that talk of the Tarutaru and Yagudo being on friendly terms is just a bunch of lies, eh?
        BUT_THE_WINDURSTIANS_SEEM_TO_BE_SAYING_IT                                     = 8870,  -- But the Windurstians seem to be saying it with a straight face...?
        AHHH_I_M_SOOO_FULL_I_JUST_ATE                                                 = 8871,  -- Ahhh, I'm sooo full! I just ate ten servings! Hahaha... Are you impressed? Well, that there restaurant sells only Tarutaru-sized servings, and ten is quite an easy amount to stomach.
        HOWEVER_THE_OWNER_WAS_TELLING_ME_THAT_DURING                                  = 8872,  -- However, the owner was telling me that during the Crystal War, there were times when a lack of rations forced the restaurant to close its doors. Can you believe it?
        IN_THE_WAR_OF_TWENTY_YEARS_AGO_WINDURST                                       = 8873,  -- In the war of twenty years ago, Windurst received a painful blow from the beastmen. Yet the constructions around here are rather new, leading one to assume these were built after the war.
        WELL_NOW_MY_SON_AND_I_CAME_TO                                                 = 8874,  -- Well now, my son and I came to view the ruins here, so we should be heading on over to Windurst Walls. They are east of here, are they not?
        WHY_DOESN_T_WINDURST_HAVE_HIGH_CASTLE_WALLS                                   = 8875,  -- Why doesn't Windurst have high castle walls like San d'Oria? They should learn how to build proper towns from us San d'Orians!
        YOU_RE_NOW_IN_WINDURST_WATERS_IF_YOU                                          = 8876,  -- You're now in Windurst Waters. If you like, I'll use my incredible magic abilities to send you over to Windurst Woods, far to the east of here.
        WARP_TO_WINDURST_WOODS_WARP_AWAY_MAYBE_ANOTHER                                = 8877,  -- Warp to Windurst Woods? Warp away! Maybe another day.
        OH_WOW_WHEN_DID_YOU_RRRECEIVE_OFFICIAL_RRRECOGNITION                          = 8878,  -- Oh, wow! When did you rrreceive official rrrecognition as an adventurrrerrr?
        WHY_ONLY_THE_OTHERRR_DAY_YOU_WERRRE_A                                         = 8879,  -- Why, only the otherrr day you werrre a novice adventurrrerrr like me. Imprrressive!
        MUNCH_MUNCH_CHEW_CHEW_WHAT_S_THAT_YOU_2                                       = 8880,  -- Munch-munch...chew-chew... What's that? You have a question you want to ask me, the man on the spot?
        I_M_THE_ACE_REPORTER_FOR_THE_MAGIC                                            = 8881,  -- I'm the ace reporter for the Magic Paradise Weekly. Why, I don't even have to move a finger. All the news just comes to me. Munch-munch...chew-chew...
        WELCOME_TO_THE_EVENSONG_RESTAURANT_THE_JOLLIEST_WAY                           = 8882,  -- Welcome to the Evensong Restaurant...the jolliest way to end the day...
        TAKE_YOUR_TIME_AND_ENJOY_SOME_OF_OUR                                          = 8883,  -- Take your time and enjoy some of our many delicious dishes.
        WELCOME_TO_THE_MORNING_STAR_RESTAURANT_THE_PERFECT                            = 8884,  -- Welcome to the Morning Star Restaurant...the perfect place to start your day.
        TAKE_A_MOMENT_TO_RELAX_AND_SAVOR_THE                                          = 8885,  -- Take a moment to relax and savor the quietude.
        WELCOME_TO_THE_BRIDGE_OF_DREAMS_RESTAURANT_THE                                = 8886,  -- Welcome to the Bridge of Dreams Restaurant...the place where your culinary desires are fulfilled.
        WE_HAVE_MANY_HEALTHY_DISHES_FOR_YOU_TO                                        = 8887,  -- We have many healthy dishes for you to try.
        WELCOME_TO_THE_CERULEAN_STAIRS_RESTAURANT_THE_CHEAPEST                        = 8888,  -- Welcome to the Cerulean Stairs Restaurant...the cheapest and tastiest place in all Windurst.
        TODAY_WE_HAVE_FRESH_SEAFOOD_BY_THE_BOATLOAD                                   = 8889,  -- Today we have fresh seafood by the boatload. Why not try our fish for lunch or dinner?
        THE_COOKING_HERRRE_IS_CARRRIED_OVERRR_FROM_THE                                = 8890,  -- The cooking herrre is carrried overrr from the Culinarrrians' Guild, so that's why the taste is top class.
        PEOPLE_COME_FROM_FARRR_AND_ABRRROAD_JUST_TO                                   = 8891,  -- People come from farrr and abrrroad just to taste ourrr dishes. Arrren't you imprrressed?
        I_M_THE_HOUSE_FLUTIST_I_DO_NIGHTLY                                            = 8892,  -- I'm the house flutist. I do nightly performances at this restaurant.
        HAVE_YOU_EVER_VISITED_US_HERE_AT_NIGHTY                                       = 8893,  -- Have you ever visited us here at nighty-nighty?
        PEOPLE_ARE_STRANGE_WHEN_IT_COMES_TO_FOOD                                      = 8894,  -- People are strange when it comes to food. It seems our tastes change with the time of day. I recommend you try our dinner dishes here too!
        PLEASE_ENJOY_SOME_SOUL_SOOTHING_MUSIC_FOR_A                                   = 8895,  -- Please enjoy some soul-soothing music for a while.
        I_M_IN_CHARRRGE_OF_THE_DAYTIME_PERRRFORRRMANCES                               = 8896,  -- I'm in charrrge of the daytime perrrforrrmances. Durrring the nights, I also enjoy listening in on Jatan-Paratan's flute perrrforrrmances.
        BY_THE_WAY_I_HOPE_MY_DAUGHTERRR_HASN                                          = 8897,  -- By the way, I hope my daughterrr hasn't offended you. She's a little rrrowdy at times...
        ENJOY_YOURRR_STAY_HERRRE                                                      = 8898,  -- Enjoy yourrr stay herrre.
        IT_TOOK_US_TWENTY_LONG_YEARS_TO_RESTORE                                       = 8899,  -- It took us twenty long years to restore our town, and just when we think we have it good, along come the rumors of war again...
        DON_T_TELL_ME_WE_NEED_TO_SACRIFICE                                            = 8900,  -- Don't tell me we need to sacrifice the lives of so many mages...not to mention the innocent lives of our wee children...?
        IF_IT_TAKES_SOME_TRIBUTE_OFFERINGS_TO_THE                                     = 8901,  -- If it takes some tribute offerings to the Yagudo to avoid a full-blown war, then I'm happy to offer it to them.
        THIS_MAY_BE_A_LITTLE_RUDE_OF_ME                                               = 8902,  -- This may be a little rude of me, but have you, my fair customer, ever listened to one of my performances?
        I_PERFORM_HERE_DURING_THE_NIGHTS_MY_JOB                                       = 8903,  -- I perform here during the nights. My job is to assist you in your enjoyment of our fine food and drinks with my dreamy-weamy melodies.
        PLEASE_STOP_BY_THE_NEXT_EVENING_YOU_ARE                                       = 8904,  -- Please stop by the next evening you are free, and enjoy the rhythm of the night.
        HAVE_YOU_MY_FAIR_CUSTOMER_EVER_LISTENED_TO                                    = 8905,  -- Have you, my fair customer, ever listened to one of my performances? If you don't mind giving your opinion, perhaps you could let me know your thoughts for my future reference.
        HOW_DID_YOU_LIKE_HIS_PERFORMANCE_IT_WAS                                       = 8906,  -- How did you like his performance? It was like music to my ears. Face the music! It wasn't so good. I have no recollection at all.
        SO_YOU_THINK_MY_PLAYING_STILL_NEEDS_WORK                                      = 8907,  -- So you think my playing still needs work?
        I_APPRECIATE_YOUR_HONEST_OPINION_I_SHALL_STRIVE                               = 8908,  -- I appreciate your honest opinion. I shall strive to continuously improve my skills.
        WHY_THANK_YOU_SO_VERY_MUCH_I_LL                                               = 8909,  -- Why, thank you so very much. I'll take that as encouragement to continuously improve my skills.
        PLEASE_STOP_BY_AND_LISTEN_AGAIN_SOME_TIME                                     = 8910,  -- Please stop by and listen again some time.
        AS_A_SIMPLE_MUSICIAN_THAT_WOULD_BE_TAKEN                                      = 8911,  -- As a simple musician that would be taken as biting criticism, but as a restaurant performer, it is the greatest of praises. Thank you very much.
        I_STRIVE_TO_CREATE_MUSIC_THAT_COMPLEMENTS_YOUR                                = 8912,  -- I strive to create music that complements your meal and doesn't distract from your conversation. Please stop by and enjoy the atmosphere again some time.
        MY_FAIR_CUSTOMER_WHAT_ARE_YOUR_THOUGHTS_ON                                    = 8913,  -- My fair customer, what are your thoughts on our restaurant here?
        I_M_SORRY_I_SHOULDN_T_HAVE_ASKED                                              = 8914,  -- I'm sorry, I shouldn't have asked that. It's not like I'm the owner of the place or anything like that...
        I_JUST_LOVE_THE_TASTES_AND_ATMOSPHERE_OF                                      = 8915,  -- I just love the tastes and atmosphere of this restaurant. I shall never forget the bliss I encountered here in the middle of my long, hard travels.
        AFTER_DISCOVERING_THIS_PLACE_I_SIMPLY_FORCED_THE                              = 8916,  -- After discovering this place, I simply forced the proprietor into allowing me to have a position here. Alas...but then...
        I_M_SORRY_I_DON_T_KNOW_WHAT                                                   = 8917,  -- ...... I'm sorry. I don't know what came over me... Please forget it.
        I_M_SORRY_I_DON_T_KNOW_WHAT_2                                                 = 8918,  -- ...... I'm sorry, I don't know what came over me... Please forget what I said.
        COME_TO_THINK_OF_IT_A_LITTLE_WHILE                                            = 8919,  -- Come to think of it, a little while back, a barrrd from Jeuno came herrre to stay forrr a spell.
        MY_MOTHERRR_SAID_THAT_EVERRR_SINCE_THAT_BARRRD                                = 8920,  -- My motherrr said that everrr since that barrrd arrrrived, Jatan-Paratan has been acting all strrrange.
        THAT_TENANT_WAS_A_HUME_WITH_THE_MOST                                          = 8921,  -- That tenant was a Hume with the most amazing facial hair I've seen!
        I_WORRRRY_ABOUT_JATAN_PARATAN_LATELY_HE_ONLY                                  = 8922,  -- I worrrry about Jatan-Paratan lately. He only performs quiet numbers now...
        BEFORE_HE_USED_TO_PLAY_CHEERFUL_TUNES_THAT                                    = 8923,  -- Before, he used to play cheerful tunes that seemed to make us forrrget about the day's fatigue. I wonder what is troubling him?
        NATURALLY_I_ALSO_AM_MOST_WORRIED_ABOUT_JATAN                                  = 8924,  -- Naturally, I also am most worried about Jatan-Paratan.
        THAT_BARD_WHO_CAME_FROM_JEUNO_THE_OTHER                                       = 8925,  -- That bard who came from Jeuno the other day appears to be an old traveling companion of his. So I assume that when they got caught up on each other's tales, he suddenly got the urge to start wandering again...?
        AH_WHAT_S_THIS_WHERE_IN_VANA_DIEL                                             = 8926,  -- Ah? What's this...? Where in Vana'diel did you get this...?
        DON_T_TELL_ME_YOU_TRAVELED_ALL_THE                                            = 8927,  -- Don't tell me you traveled all the way to Jeuno to meet Ruslan! Why would you do such a thing?
        WHAT_YUNG_AND_YULI_YAAM_WERE_WORRIED_THAT                                     = 8928,  -- What? Yung and Yuli Yaam were worried that I'm not myself of late...
        I_AM_SINCERELY_TOUCHED_BY_THE_FACT_YOU                                        = 8929,  -- I am sincerely touched by the fact you all care so much about me...
        ALLOW_ME_TO_SHARE_MY_HEARTFELT_FEELINGS_WITH                                  = 8930,  -- Allow me to share my heartfelt feelings with you...
        TWAS_A_LITTLE_WHILE_AGO_THAT_RUSLAN_AN                                        = 8931,  -- 'Twas a little while ago that Ruslan, an old acquaintance who practiced music with me, came to this very tavern and let me hear of his recent tales.
        HE_PRAISED_MY_PERFORMANCE_GREATLY_BUT_HAD_NO                                  = 8932,  -- He praised my performance greatly, but had no interest in the food of this restaurant.
        DESPITE_SOJOURNING_HERE_FOR_SEVERAL_WEEKS_AND_EATING                          = 8933,  -- Despite sojourning here for several weeks and eating the food here every night, he couldn't remember the slightest thing about the restaurant's cooking.
        TWAS_THEN_THAT_I_REALIZED_THAT_MY_FLAMBOYANT                                  = 8934,  -- 'Twas then that I realized that my flamboyant performance itself was detracting from the tastes and atmosphere of this tavern.
        IT_WAS_LIKE_I_WAS_REPAYING_THE_TAVERN                                         = 8935,  -- It was like I was repaying the tavern owner's kindness with evil...or biting the hand that feeds me--no, everyone...
        AND_SO_NOW_I_M_SEARCHING_WITHIN_MYSELF                                        = 8936,  -- And so now I'm searching within myself for a more appropriate sound. Alas, I've been unable to find it yet.
        I_APOLOGIZE_FOR_THE_TROUBLE_I_VE_CAUSED                                       = 8937,  -- I apologize for the trouble I've caused...drawing you into my own personal problems...problems that shouldn't concern one as esteemed as yourself.
        BUT_YES_INDEED_THIS_WAS_ONCE_THE_GOAL                                         = 8938,  -- But, yes indeed, this was once the goal I sought after. I shall gladly accept it from you. However, let me pay you back with this...
        THAT_IS_ALSO_A_LITTLE_SOMETHING_I_COLLECTED                                   = 8939,  -- That is also a little something I collected while I was first obsessed with music.
        I_WAS_GOING_TO_THROW_IT_AWAY_BUT                                              = 8940,  -- I was going to throw it away, but I suppose if one were to sell it, it would fetch quite a sum. Please take it. I hope it assists you in your travels.
        I_BEG_YOUR_PARDON_BUT_IF_YOU_DON                                              = 8941,  -- I beg your pardon, but, if you don't mind...could we kindly keep this between you and me, and not bother Yung and Yuli Yaam with my problems?
        I_DON_T_WANT_TO_WORRY_THEM_ANY                                                = 8942,  -- I don't want to worry them any further with my problems. It might affect Yuli's philosophy towards music...
        I_JUST_LOVE_YULI_YAAM_S_MUSIC                                                 = 8943,  -- I just love Yuli Yaam's music.
        PERHAPS_IT_IS_SELFISH_OF_ME_BUT_WHEN                                          = 8944,  -- Perhaps it is selfish of me, but when I first came here midway through my journeys, I wished both this place and its music would stay the same.
        I_DON_T_KNOW_WHAT_IS_BOTHERRRING_JATAN                                        = 8945,  -- I don't know what is botherrring Jatan-Paratan, but I've decided to carrrry on as if nothing has changed.
        I_HOPE_THAT_MY_WARRRM_HEARRRTED_MUSIC_WILL                                    = 8946,  -- I hope that my warrrm-hearrrted music will prrrovide him with morrre comforrrt and encourrragement than worrrds can...
        I_HOPE_MY_HARRRP_CAN_EASE_JATAN_PARATAN                                       = 8947,  -- I hope my harrrp can ease Jatan-Paratan's melancholy hearrrt, even a little.
        MOTHERRR_IS_SUCH_A_WORRRRIERRR_JATAN_PARATAN_SEEMS                            = 8948,  -- Motherrr is such a worrrrierrr! Jatan-Paratan seems his same old self again to me.
        BUT_I_MUST_SAY_THAT_I_DID_PRRREFERRR                                          = 8949,  -- But I must say that I did prrreferrr the cheerrrful little ditties Jatan-Paratan used to play beforrre. They werrre morrre my type of music.t
        EACH_AND_EVERY_ONE_OF_US_HAVE_THEIR                                           = 8950,  -- Each and every one of us have their own problems. But such is the spice of life...
        WELCOME_TO_THE_RESTAURANT_THAT_RESOUNDS_WITH_ITS                              = 8951,  -- Welcome to the restaurant that resounds with its own sound! Welcome to the Timbre Timbers Tavern!
        WELCOME_TO_MY_LITTLE_CATALYST_SHOP_WHERE_YOU                                  = 8952,  -- Welcome to my little catalyst shop, where you'll find a range of general and unusual goods!
        FOR_ADVENTURERRRS_ON_THE_GO_ENSASA_S_CATALYST                                 = 8953,  -- For adventurerrrs on the go, Ensasa's Catalyst Shop is the place for all you need in generrral goods!
        ERG_I_M_SOOO_BUSY_WUSY_I_THOUGHT                                              = 8954,  -- Erg! I'm sooo busy-wusy! I thought this job would be a great way to meetaru people, but they've got me out in the backy-wacky all day doing odd jobs!
        OH_HIDEY_WIDEY_THIS_IS_THE_FEDERAL_MAGIC                                      = 8955,  -- Oh, hidey-widey! This is the Federal Magic Reservey-wervey. What can I do for you today-oway?
        WELCOME_TO_THE_FEDERAL_MAGIC_RESERVE_THE_ONLY                                 = 8956,  -- Welcome to the Federal Magic Reserve, the only place in the Federation where high-level magic is allowed to be sold.
        WELCOME_TO_BAREN_MOREN_S_MAKERS_OF_THE                                        = 8957,  -- Welcome to Baren-Moren's, makers of the finest headwear. Our slogan is: The smarter the hat, the smarter the head.
        HE_HE_HE_I_VE_GOT_STUFF_GOING                                                 = 8958,  -- He-he-he... I've got stuff going cheap.
        MAY_I_TAKE_YOUR_ORDER_PLEASE                                                  = 8959,  -- May I take your order, please...
        PSST_CHECK_OUT_THESE_THINGS_MY_SUPPLIERS_IN                                   = 8960,  -- Psst... Check out these things my suppliers in Aragoneu dug up.
        SORRRRY_BUT_I_M_WAITING_ON_MY_NEXT                                            = 8961,  -- Sorrrry, but I'm waiting on my next shipment from Aragoneu, so I'm all out of things to sell you at the moment.
        CAN_I_INTEREST_YOU_IN_SOME_OF_SARUTABARUTA                                    = 8962,  -- Can I interest you in some of Sarutabaruta's wares? Come on, have a look, and see how I fares!t
        SORRY_DORRY_BUT_I_M_TAKING_A_BREAKY                                           = 8963,  -- Sorry-dorry, but I'm taking a breaky-wakey! (Or, as you'll be knowing, since control of Sarutabaruta was lost, I'm out of stock, so go on, get going!)t
        PSST_WANNA_BUY_SOMETHIN_CHEAP_FROM_KOLSHUSHU                                  = 8964,  -- Psst... Wanna buy somethin' cheap from Kolshushu?
        HEE_HEE_HEE_CAN_YOU_HANG_ON_A                                                 = 8965,  -- Hee-hee-hee... Can you hang on a while? I can start selling you good stuff from Kolshushu once I'm ready.
        HELLO_ADVENTURER_CAN_I_INTEREST_YOU_IN_SOMETHING                              = 8966,  -- Hello, adventurer! Can I interest you in something a little different--something from Elshimo?
        WELL_UM_LET_ME_SEE_THIS_SHOULD_BE                                             = 8967,  -- Well, um, let me see... This should be a good spot to open shop. There are some wealthy-looking Tarutaru houses nearby. It's quiet and yet there're plenty of passers-by...
        HE_HE_HE_HEY_HOW_S_ABOUT_ITEMS                                                = 8968,  -- He-he-he... Hey! How's about... Items from Li'Telor that you can't do without? Reckon you could do, with one of these or two?t
        OH_PHEW_MY_HEART_IS_SO_BLUE_BLUER                                             = 8969,  -- Oh... Phew... My heart is so blue... Bluer than these flowers... Leave me be for a couple hours...
        GREETINGS_CAN_I_INTEREST_YOU_IN_SOME_OF                                       = 8970,  -- Greetings. Can I interest you in some of these goods from Ronfaure...?
        GREETINGS_I_AM_JOURILLE_YOUR_FRIENDLY_NEIGHBORHOOD_TRAVELING                  = 8971,  -- Greetings! I am Jourille, your friendly neighborhood traveling merchant. I would most like to sell you something from Ronfaure right now, but I regret that I am waiting on my next shipment. Please call by later!
        WHO_THE_HELL_ARE_YOU_DID_YOU_KNOW                                             = 8972,  -- Who the hell are you? Did you know that this residence belongs to the unspeakably rich Honoi-Gomoi--oh, that's me, you know!--before you so rudely barged in?
        I_M_ROLLING_IN_MONEY_BUT_I_HAVEN                                              = 8973,  -- I'm rolling in money, but I haven't a single gil to give to the likes of you! Get out of here! Go on... Shoo, shoo!
        PRODUCERS_ONLY_OPENING_EVENTS_MISSION_RELATED_WARP_SAW                        = 8974,  -- PRODUCERS ONLY!!! OPENING EVENTS MISSION-RELATED. WARP. SAW OPENING EVENT. CHEAT ON FAME. RESET ALLNITIAL SETTINGS. EX MISSIONS
        WHERE_YOU_WANNA_WARP_HATTER_S_CULINARIANS_GUILD                               = 8975,  -- WHERE YOU WANNA WARP? HATTER'S. CULINARIANS' GUILD. ARTIST'S. RESTAURANT. RHINOSTERY (LAB). RHINOSTERY2 (MEDITATION RM.). RHINOSTERY3 (STAIRS). AURASTERY (STAFF ROOM). AURASTERY (ADV. CLASS). HOSTEL. HOUSE. HOUSE (MR). TRADER'S HOUSE. OPTISTERY (MAGIC LIBRARY). OPTISTERY (MANUSCRIPT LIBRARY). OPTISTERY (2F). CENTER. MAGAZINE PUBLISHER'S.
        GATHER_AROUND_WHERE_HATTER_S_CULINARIANS_GUILD_ARTIST                         = 8976,  -- GATHER AROUND WHERE? HATTER'S. CULINARIANS'GUILD. ARTIST'S. RESTAURANT. RHINOSTERY. AURASTERY. INN. TRADER'S HOUSE. HOUSE. PASSERS-BY.
        RECALL_WORKED                                                                 = 8977,  -- RECALL WORKED!
