        THE_WINNER_IS                                                                 = 14879,  -- The winner is %!
        SOMEONE_HAS_DROPPED_THE_DIE_DOWN_THE_DRAIN                                    = 14880,  -- Someone has dropped the die down the drain! You can no longer continue playing.
        THE_FINAL_PLACE_AT_THE_TABLE_HAS_ALREADY                                      = 14881,  -- The final place at the table has already been taken.
        YOU_DO_NOT_HAVE_ENOUGH_GIL_3                                                  = 14882,  -- You do not have enough gil.
        SOMEONE_HAS_DROPPED_THE_DIE                                                   = 14883,  -- Someone has dropped the die!
        READ_WHICH_CHAPTER_1_THE_HEART_OF_VENTURE                                     = 14884,  -- Read which chapter? 1. The Heart of Venture Roll.. Rules of the Roll.. Putting the Book Down.
        VENTURE_ROLL_IS_A_COMPETITIVE_GAME_PLAYED_WITH                                = 14885,  -- Venture roll is a competitive game played with dice similar to those used by corsairs. The objective is to roll until your cumulative total comes as close to 11 as possible without going over.
        UNTIL_YOU_REACH_OR_GO_OVER_11_YOU                                             = 14886,  -- Until you reach or go over 11, you may continue rolling (doubling up) as many times as the table time limit allows (# [minute/minutes], Earth time).
        IN_ADDITION_TO_DOUBLING_UP_YOU_MAY_ALSO                                       = 14887,  -- In addition to doubling up, you may also decline to roll the dice and stay with your current total (hold fast).
        IF_YOUR_TOTAL_EVER_GOES_OVER_11_YOU                                           = 14888,  -- If your total ever goes over 11, you will automatically lose the game, regardless of the totals of other players. Knowing the right time to hold fast is one of the keys to staying in the match.
        ONCE_ALL_THE_PLAYERS_HAVE_HELD_FAST_THE                                       = 14889,  -- Once all the players have held fast, the game is over and the results are announced. The player closest to 11 is declared the winner and receives all the gil in the pot (the original participation fees of all the players).
        OBJECTIVE_ROLL_A_SIX_SIDED_DIE_AS_MANY                                        = 14890,  -- Objective: Roll a six-sided die as many times as necessary to achieve a total as close to 11 as possible. You lose the instant your total exceeds 11.
        IF_TWO_OR_MORE_PLAYERS_ARE_THE_CLOSEST                                        = 14891,  -- If two or more players are the closest to 11 at the end of a match, the game is considered a draw and all participation fees are repaid in full.
        ONCE_THE_GAME_HAS_STARTED_FEES_WILL_NOT                                       = 14892,  -- Once the game has started, fees will not be refunded for any reason unless the match results in a draw.
        IT_S_HERE_IT_S_HERE_THE_SEASON                                                = 14893,  -- It's here! It's here! The season of Celestial Nights is upon us! And to celebrate, the moogles are bringing together lost loves by offering free teleportation to San d'Oria, Bastok, and Windurst!
        IF_THERE_S_SOMEONE_YOU_VE_BEEN_LONGING                                        = 14894,  -- If there's someone you've been longing to see, just let me know and I'll warp you right to their side (provided they are in either San d'Oria, Bastok, or Windurst), kupo!
        WHERE_WOULD_YOU_LIKE_TO_GO_NOWHERE_SAN                                        = 14895,  -- Where would you like to go? Nowhere. San d'Oria. Bastok. Windurst.
        SEE_YOU_AGAIN_KUPO                                                            = 14896,  -- See you again, kupo!
        OH_THAT_S_RIGHT_I_ALMOST_FORGOT_TO                                            = 14897,  -- Oh, that's right! I almost forgot to give you this, kupo!
        ARE_YOU_READY_FOR_ANOTHER_SPINE_CHILLING_STOMACH                              = 14898,  -- Are you ready for another spine-chilling, stomach-churning test of your mettle, kupo!?
        WE_VE_SET_UP_A_SECRET_MARKER_SOMEWHERE_2                                      = 14899,  -- We've set up a secret marker somewhere in the bowels of a dreadful dungeon. Your goal is to reach that marker alive, kupo!
        OH_A_NEW_ADVENTURER_BEST_OF_LUCK_KUPO_2                                       = 14900,  -- Oh, a new adventurer! Best of luck, kupo!
        ARE_YOU_HELPING_OUT_THE_NEW_ADVENTURERS_BEST_2                                = 14901,  -- Are you helping out the new adventurers? Best of luck in your endeavors, kupo!
        HERE_S_YOUR_REWARD_FOR_REACHING_THE_GOAL_2                                    = 14902,  -- Here's your reward for reaching the goal, kupo!
        THE_FACE_IN_THE_PORTRAIT_YOU_BROUGHT_ME_2                                     = 14903,  -- The face in the portrait you brought me is just... Kupupupu!
        YOU_TOOK_ANOTHER_DIVE_INTO_THE_DREADED_DUNGEON_2                              = 14904,  -- You took another dive into the dreaded dungeon, kupo? Well, you deserve a little something for your preternatural perseverance, kupo.
        THIS_ISN_T_ENOUGH_TO_PROVE_YOU_REACHED_2                                      = 14905,  -- This isn't enough to prove you reached the goal as a dungeon-delving duo. You have to bring me the item your partner received to show that you were both successful, kupo!
        TO_GO_ON_THIS_FRIGHT_FILLED_FACE_OFF_2                                        = 14906,  -- To go on this fright-filled face-off with fear, you need a partner who can prove you reached the goal. Come back when you have a buddy in bravery, kupo!
        THIS_ADVENTURE_INTO_ADVERSITY_IS_ONLY_AVAILABLE_TO_2                          = 14907,  -- This adventure into adversity is only available to two-person parties. Split up into pairs and talk to me again, kupo!
        PLEASE_COME_BACK_WITH_A_DIFFERENT_PARTNER_IT_2                                = 14908,  -- Please come back with a different partner. It'll be no fun to scare you if your reactions are too similar, kupo!
        YOUR_PARTNER_ISN_T_READY_TO_GO_PLEASE_2                                       = 14909,  -- Your partner isn't ready to go. Please wait a little longer, kupo.
        YOUR_PARTNER_MUST_TALK_TO_ME_AS_WELL_2                                        = 14910,  -- Your partner must talk to me as well. I'll be waiting for you whenever you're ready, kupo.
        YOU_CAN_ONLY_CHOOSE_ONE_PARTNER_A_DAY_2                                       = 14911,  -- You can only choose one partner a day. Come back again tomorrow, kupo!
        HOLD_UP_THERE_IT_LOOKS_LIKE_YOUR_CANDIDATE_2                                  = 14912,  -- Hold up there! It looks like your candidate for courageous companionship has already got a partner! You can't choose that person at the moment, kupo!
        PLEASE_WAIT_A_LITTLE_LONGER_OR_FIND_A_2                                       = 14913,  -- Please wait a little longer or find a new partner before coming back, kupo.
        ARE_YOU_READY_TO_TEST_YOUR_COURAGE_KUPO_2                                     = 14914,  -- Are you ready to test your courage, kupo?
        ARE_YOU_READY_TO_GO_READY_KUPO_I_2                                            = 14915,  -- Are you ready to go? Ready, kupo! I'm too terrified, kupo!
        I_LL_BE_CHECKING_TO_SEE_IF_YOU_2                                              = 14916,  -- I'll be checking to see if you reached the goal. You can use this magical scroll to make a speedy return to town, kupo.
        IF_YOU_BOTH_SUCCEED_I_LL_HAVE_A_2                                             = 14917,  -- If you both succeed, I'll have a prize waiting for you! Now, off you go, kupo!
        YOU_CAN_ONLY_CARRY_ONE_2                                                      = 14918,  -- You can only carry one %.
        ARE_YOU_PARTICIPATING_IN_THIS_PETRIFYING_PILGRIMAGE_WITH_2                    = 14919,  -- Are you participating in this petrifying pilgrimage with the person in your present party?
        HEY_YOU_CHANGED_PARTNERS_YOU_CAN_T_SWITCH_2                                   = 14920,  -- Hey, you changed partners! You can't switch halfway through, kupo!
        WAIT_THE_NUMBER_OF_PEOPLE_IN_YOUR_PARTY_2                                     = 14921,  -- Wait, the number of people in your party has changed! You have to be in a two-person party, kupo!
        CHOOSE_YOUR_PARTNER_WISELY_COME_BACK_WHEN_YOU_2                               = 14922,  -- Choose your partner wisely. Come back when you think you have a winning combo, kupo!
        YOU_THERE_I_SUPPOSE_YOU_VE_HEARD_THE_2                                        = 14923,  -- You there. I suppose you've heard the gossip flying around town--the talk of part-time ghosts?
        HAVE_YOU_HEARD_YES_I_VE_HEARD_PART                                            = 14924,  -- Have you heard? Yes, I've heard. Part-time ghosts!?
        THEN_WE_MAY_MOVE_ON_TO_MORE_IMPORTANT_2                                       = 14925,  -- Then we may move on to more important matters.
        WE_HAVEN_T_BEEN_ABLE_TO_LOCATE_ENOUGH                                         = 14926,  -- We haven't been able to locate enough volunteers to participate in this year's festivities, and are searching for adventurers who would be willing to aid us.
        ALL_YOU_WILL_BE_REQUIRED_TO_DO_IS                                             = 14927,  -- All you will be required to do is dress up in one of these frightening costumes and wander about the city with the other specters.
        SIGH_THEN_ALLOW_ME_TO_EXPLAIN                                                 = 14928,  -- <Sigh>... Then allow me to explain.
        A_MEMORIAL_IS_CURRENTLY_BEING_HELD_IN_HONOR                                   = 14929,  -- A memorial is currently being held in honor of a long-lost coven of witches known as the Dark Lilies.
        DURING_THE_MEMORIAL_VOLUNTEERS_DRESSED_UP_AS_THE                              = 14930,  -- During the memorial, volunteers dressed up as the witches and spirits walk a course about the city in honor of the deceased.
        HOWEVER_WHILE_WE_HAVE_FILLED_ALL_THE_SPOTS                                    = 14931,  -- However, while we have filled all the spots for the witches, we are quite short on people willing to play the part of the monsters who follow the Lilies.
        WOULD_YOU_BE_WILLING_TO_LEND_A_HAND                                           = 14932,  -- Would you be willing to lend a hand, fine sir/lady]?
        WILL_YOU_HELP_OF_COURSE_NOT_A_GHOST_2                                         = 14933,  -- Will you help? Of course. Not a ghost of a chance.
        AH_HOW_DROLL_PLEASE_SPEAK_WITH_ME_AGAIN                                       = 14934,  -- Ah... How droll. Please speak with me again if you change your mind.
        MOST_EXCELLENT_THERE_IS_ONE_THING_YOU_MUST_2                                  = 14935,  -- Most excellent. There is one thing you must be aware of, however.
        THE_WITCHES_HAVE_THE_MOST_IMPORTANT_ROLE_IN                                   = 14936,  -- The witches have the most important role in this memorial service. You are to tread only in their wake. If it is found that you have stepped ahead of one of the Lilies, you will be asked to return your costume and leave the procession.
        THOUGH_WE_ARE_A_FORGIVING_ORGANIZATION_AND_IF                                 = 14937,  -- Though, we are a forgiving organization, and if you wish to participate once again, either speak with me or simply put on another costume and your request shall be granted.
        AH_YES_AND_ONE_MORE_THING_THERE_ARE                                           = 14938,  -- Ah yes, and one more thing. There are two citizens playing the parts of the witches Guwanana and Bikho Ronpotteh.
        YOU_ARE_TO_FOLLOW_THE_FAIR_MITHRAN_MAID                                       = 14939,  -- You are to follow the fair Mithran maid dressed as Bikho. Remember this, as you will not receive any compensation in the event you join the wrong group.
        AH_WELCOME_BACK_ADVENTURER_YOU_HAVE_DONE_WELL                                 = 14940,  -- Ah, welcome back, adventurer. You have done well. The Dark Lilies would be pleased.
        PLEASE_TAKE_THIS_AS_A_TOKEN_OF_OUR                                            = 14941,  -- Please take this as a token of our appreciation.
        IT_IS_A_HAT_MODELED_AFTER_THOSE_WORN                                          = 14942,  -- It is a hat modeled after those worn by the Dark Lilies. Perhaps you might wear it during the season's festivities.
        OH_AND_SHOULD_YOU_WISH_TO_AID_US                                              = 14943,  -- Oh, and should you wish to aid us again, we would welcome your help. Many thanks, %.
        WHAT_HAS_BEFALLEN_YOU_DO_YOU_WISH_TO_2                                        = 14944,  -- What has befallen you? Do you wish to give up?
        GIVE_UP_I_M_DONE_NOT_YET_2                                                    = 14945,  -- Give up? I'm done. Not yet.
        A_PITY_PLEASE_SPEAK_WITH_ME_AGAIN_IF_2                                        = 14946,  -- A pity. Please speak with me again if you change your mind.
        YOU_ARE_TO_FOLLOW_THE_YOUNG_MAIDEN_DRESSED                                    = 14947,  -- You are to follow the young maiden dressed as Guwanana. Remember this, as you will not receive any compensation in the event you join the wrong group.
        GOOD_DAY_I_SUPPOSE_YOU_VE_HEARD_OF_2                                          = 14948,  -- Good day! I suppose you've heard of all the people signing up to play ghosts in this year's festival, nay?
        HAVE_YOU_HEARD_YES_I_VE_HEARD_PLAY                                            = 14949,  -- Have you heard? Yes, I've heard. Play ghosts!?
        I_WOULDN_T_EXPECT_ANYTHING_LESS_FROM_AN_2                                     = 14950,  -- I wouldn't expect anything less from an adventurer.
        I_LL_GET_STRAIGHT_TO_THE_POINT_THEN                                           = 14951,  -- I'll get straight to the point, then. We need volunteers to dress up as ghosts, specters, wights, and the like, and walk around the city in honor of the Dark Lilies.
        WOULD_YOU_BE_WILLING_TO_PARTICIPATE_YOU_WILL                                  = 14952,  -- Would you be willing to participate? You will be rewarded nicely!
        WELL_YOU_ADVENTURERS_ARE_PRETTY_BUSY_I_GUESS_2                                = 14953,  -- Well, you adventurers are pretty busy, I guess. Let me give you the short version:
        WE_RE_PUTTING_ON_A_GRAND_PARADE_FOR                                           = 14954,  -- We're putting on a grand parade for this season's Harvest Festival.
        WE_ALREADY_HAVE_ENOUGH_PEOPLE_TO_PLAY_THE                                     = 14955,  -- We already have enough people to play the witches, but there can never be enough monsters, nay?
        THAT_S_WHY_WE_NEED_VOLUNTEERS_LIKE_YOU                                        = 14956,  -- That's why we need volunteers like you to make the parade even more exciting. Oh, worry not, adventurer. You will be rewarded nicely!
        WILL_YOU_HELP_OF_COURSE_NOT_A_GHOST_3                                         = 14957,  -- Will you help? Of course. Not a ghost of a chance.
        OH_WELL_ACTING_ISN_T_EVERYBODY_S_CUP                                          = 14958,  -- Oh... Well, acting isn't everybody's cup of tea. I'll be here if you change your mind.
        THANK_YOU_NOW_THERE_IS_ONE_THING_YOU                                          = 14959,  -- Thank you! Now, there is one thing you should know...
        THE_WITCHES_LEAD_THE_PROCESSION_IF_YOU_START                                  = 14960,  -- The witches lead the procession. If you start getting any delusions of grandeur and work your way in front of the Lilies, you will be required to turn over your costume and forfeit all payment for services up to that point.
        BUT_THAT_DOESN_T_MEAN_YOU_CAN_T                                               = 14961,  -- But that doesn't mean you can't try again! Just put on another costume and get back in line. I'm sure you'll get the hang of things soon enough.
        OH_AND_ONE_MORE_THING_THERE_ARE_TWO                                           = 14962,  -- Oh, and one more thing. There are two witches in this season's parade: Selma and Pretty Heart.
        YOU_RE_TO_BE_STATIONED_IN_SELMA_S                                             = 14963,  -- You're to be stationed in Selma's parade, so don't go wandering over to Pretty Heart's, hear me?
        GOOD_LUCK_6                                                                   = 14964,  -- Good luck!
        EXCELLENT_JOB_YOU_VE_DONE_THE_WITCHES_PROUD                                   = 14965,  -- Excellent job, %! You've done the witches proud.
        HERE_S_THE_REWARD_I_PROMISED                                                  = 14966,  -- Here's the reward I promised.
        IT_S_A_WITCH_HAT_THE_DESIGN_MATCHES_2                                         = 14967,  -- It's a witch hat. The design matches those worn by the Dark Lilies. Put it on, and go have fun. Forget about ghosts for a while.
        THOUGH_IF_YOU_WANT_TO_VOLUNTEER_AGAIN_I                                       = 14968,  -- Though, if you want to volunteer again, I'll be right here waiting for you!
        GIVING_UP_THE_GHOST_EH                                                        = 14969,  -- Giving up the ghost, eh?
        OH_WELL_ACTING_ISN_T_EVERYBODY_S_CUP_2                                        = 14970,  -- Oh... Well, acting isn't everybody's cup of tea. I'll be here if you change your mind.
        YOU_RE_TO_BE_STATIONED_IN_PRETTY_HEART                                        = 14971,  -- You're to be stationed in Pretty Heart's parade, so don't go wandering over to Selma's, hear me?
        HI_I_M_GERTRUDE_I_M_HELPING_WITH                                              = 14972,  -- Hi, I'm Gertrude. I'm helping with some of the Harvest Festival activities. Have you heard about our hiring policies?
        HEARD_ABOUT_THEM_YES_NOT_AT_ALL                                               = 14973,  -- Heard about them? Yes. Not at all.
        YOU_HAVE_WELL_THAT_MAKES_MY_JOB_EASIER_2                                      = 14974,  -- You have? Well, that makes my job easier, then.
        SO_WOULD_YOU_LIKE_TO_SIGN_UP_FOR                                              = 14975,  -- So, would you like to sign up for the Procession of the Lilies?
        NO_THEN_LET_ME_FILL_YOU_IN_ON_2                                               = 14976,  -- No? Then let me fill you in on the details. We are currently holding a memorial for the Dark Lilies, in which two women dressed as members of the lost coven lead a party of spirits around the city.
        THERE_IS_A_SHORTAGE_OF_VOLUNTEERS_FOR_THE                                     = 14977,  -- There is a shortage of volunteers for the witches' undead followers, and I was wondering if you would like to help.
        SIGN_UP_RIGHT_AWAY_NOT_TODAY                                                  = 14978,  -- Sign up? Right away! Not today.
        ADVENTURERS_ARE_OFTEN_VERY_BUSY_OR_SO_I_2                                     = 14979,  -- Adventurers are often very busy, or so I've heard. Please come back if you change your mind.
        WONDERFUL_THERE_ARE_JUST_TWO_MORE_THINGS_I                                    = 14980,  -- Wonderful. There are just two more things I must warn you of, however.
        FIRST_AND_FOREMOST_DURING_THE_PROCESSION_THE_WITCHES                          = 14981,  -- First and foremost, during the procession, the witches are boss, so don't even think of stepping in front of them. If you do, your costume will be immediately confiscated.
        AH_BUT_IF_THAT_HAPPENS_YOU_NEED_NOT                                           = 14982,  -- Ah, but if that happens, you need not worry. Just put on another costume and try again!
        SECONDLY_THERE_ARE_TWO_WITCHES_IN_THE_CITY                                    = 14983,  -- Secondly, there are two witches in the city--Maryse and Poseaulloie.
        YOU_ARE_TO_JOIN_WITH_POSEAULLOIE_S_CONGREGATION                               = 14984,  -- You are to join with Poseaulloie's congregation.
        GOOD_LUCK_7                                                                   = 14985,  -- Good luck!
        HOW_DID_YOU_FARE_WAS_THE_WITCH_PLEASED                                        = 14986,  -- How did you fare...? Was the witch pleased?
        EITHER_WAY_YOUR_HELP_HAS_BEEN_INVALUABLE_WOULD                                = 14987,  -- Either way, your help has been invaluable. Would you accept this in appreciation?
        IT_S_A_WITCH_HAT_PLEASE_WEAR_IT_2                                             = 14988,  -- It's a witch hat. Please wear it in the festivities and forget about ghosts and spirits for a while...
        THOUGH_IF_YOU_HAVE_TIME_WE_WOULD_GLADLY                                       = 14989,  -- Though, if you have time, we would gladly accept your help again.
        WHAT_S_WRONG_HAVE_YOU_GROWN_TIRED_OF_2                                        = 14990,  -- What's wrong? Have you grown tired of your duties?
        OH_I_SEE_WELL_PLEASE_RETURN_TO_ME_2                                           = 14991,  -- Oh, I see... Well, please return to me if you find your patience for them restored.
        YOU_ARE_TO_JOIN_WITH_MARYSE_S_CONGREGATION                                    = 14992,  -- You are to join with Maryse's congregation.
        I_SHALL_LET_YOU_KNOW_WHEN_THERE_IS                                            = 14993,  -- I shall let you know when there is another opening.
